54void swap( Mat& a, Mat& b )
55{
56 std::swap(a.flags, b.flags);
57 std::swap(a.dims, b.dims);
58 std::swap(a.rows, b.rows);
59 std::swap(a.cols, b.cols);
60 std::swap(a.data, b.data);
61 std::swap(a.refcount, b.refcount);
62 std::swap(a.datastart, b.datastart);
63 std::swap(a.dataend, b.dataend);
64 std::swap(a.datalimit, b.datalimit);
65 std::swap(a.allocator, b.allocator);
66
67 std::swap(a.size.p, b.size.p);
68 std::swap(a.step.p, b.step.p);
69 std::swap(a.step.buf[0], b.step.buf[0]);
70 std::swap(a.step.buf[1], b.step.buf[1]);
71
72 if( a.step.p == b.step.buf )
73 {
74 a.step.p = a.step.buf;
75 a.size.p = &a.rows;
76 }
77
78 if( b.step.p == a.step.buf )
79 {
80 b.step.p = b.step.buf;
81 b.size.p = &b.rows;
82 }
83}

86static inline void setSize( Mat& m, int _dims, const int* _sz,
87 const size_t* _steps, bool autoSteps=false )
88{
89 CV_Assert( 0 <= _dims && _dims <= CV_MAX_DIM );
90 if( m.dims != _dims )
91 {
92 if( m.step.p != m.step.buf )
93 {
94 fastFree(m.step.p);
95 m.step.p = m.step.buf;
96 m.size.p = &m.rows;
97 }
98 if( _dims > 2 )
99 {
100 m.step.p = (size_t*)fastMalloc(_dims*sizeof(m.step.p[0]) + (_dims+1)*sizeof(m.size.p[0]));
101 m.size.p = (int*)(m.step.p + _dims) + 1;
102 m.size.p[-1] = _dims;
103 m.rows = m.cols = -1;
104 }
105 }
106
107 m.dims = _dims;
108 if( !_sz )
109 return;
110
111 size_t esz = CV_ELEM_SIZE(m.flags), total = esz;
112 int i;
113 for( i = _dims-1; i >= 0; i-- )
114 {
115 int s = _sz[i];
116 CV_Assert( s >= 0 );
117 m.size.p[i] = s;
118
119 if( _steps )
120 m.step.p[i] = i < _dims-1 ? _steps[i] : esz;
121 else if( autoSteps )
122 {
123 m.step.p[i] = total;
124 int64 total1 = (int64)total*s;
125 if( (uint64)total1 != (size_t)total1 )
126 CV_Error( CV_StsOutOfRange, "The total matrix size does not fit to \"size_t\" type" );
127 total = (size_t)total1;
128 }
129 }
130
131 if( _dims == 1 )
132 {
133 m.dims = 2;
134 m.cols = 1;
135 m.step[1] = esz;
136 }
137}
138
139static void updateContinuityFlag(Mat& m)
140{
141 int i, j;
142 for( i = 0; i < m.dims; i++ )
143 {
144 if( m.size[i] > 1 )
145 break;
146 }
147
148 for( j = m.dims-1; j > i; j-- )
149 {
150 if( m.step[j]*m.size[j] < m.step[j-1] )
151 break;
152 }
153
154 uint64 t = (uint64)m.step[0]*m.size[0];
155 if( j <= i && t == (size_t)t )
156 m.flags |= Mat::CONTINUOUS_FLAG;
157 else
158 m.flags &= ~Mat::CONTINUOUS_FLAG;
159}
160
161static void finalizeHdr(Mat& m)
162{
163 updateContinuityFlag(m);
164 int d = m.dims;
165 if( d > 2 )
166 m.rows = m.cols = -1;
167 if( m.data )
168 {
169 m.datalimit = m.datastart + m.size[0]*m.step[0];
170 if( m.size[0] > 0 )
171 {
172 m.dataend = m.data + m.size[d-1]*m.step[d-1];
173 for( int i = 0; i < d-1; i++ )
174 m.dataend += (m.size[i] - 1)*m.step[i];
175 }
176 else
177 m.dataend = m.datalimit;
178 }
179 else
180 m.dataend = m.datalimit = 0;
181}

184void Mat::create(int d, const int* _sizes, int _type)
185{
186 int i;
187 CV_Assert(0 <= d && d <= CV_MAX_DIM && _sizes);
188 _type = CV_MAT_TYPE(_type);
189
190 if( data && (d == dims || (d == 1 && dims <= 2)) && _type == type() )
191 {
192 if( d == 2 && rows == _sizes[0] && cols == _sizes[1] )
193 return;
194 for( i = 0; i < d; i++ )
195 if( size[i] != _sizes[i] )
196 break;
197 if( i == d && (d > 1 || size[1] == 1))
198 return;
199 }
200
201 release();
202 if( d == 0 )
203 return;
204 flags = (_type & CV_MAT_TYPE_MASK) | MAGIC_VAL;
205 setSize(*this, d, _sizes, 0, true);
206
207 if( total() > 0 )
208 {
209#ifdef HAVE_TGPU
210 if( !allocator || allocator == tegra::getAllocator() ) allocator = tegra::getAllocator(d, _sizes, _type);
211#endif
212 if( !allocator )
213 {
214 size_t totalsize = alignSize(step.p[0]*size.p[0], (int)sizeof(*refcount));
215 data = datastart = (uchar*)fastMalloc(totalsize + (int)sizeof(*refcount));
216 refcount = (int*)(data + totalsize);
217 *refcount = 1;
218 }
219 else
220 {
221#ifdef HAVE_TGPU
222 try
223 {
224 allocator->allocate(dims, size, _type, refcount, datastart, data, step.p);
225 CV_Assert( step[dims-1] == (size_t)CV_ELEM_SIZE(flags) );
226 }catch(...)
227 {
228 allocator = 0;
229 size_t totalSize = alignSize(step.p[0]*size.p[0], (int)sizeof(*refcount));
230 data = datastart = (uchar*)fastMalloc(totalSize + (int)sizeof(*refcount));
231 refcount = (int*)(data + totalSize);
232 *refcount = 1;
233 }
234#else
235 allocator->allocate(dims, size, _type, refcount, datastart, data, step.p);
236 CV_Assert( step[dims-1] == (size_t)CV_ELEM_SIZE(flags) );
237#endif
238 }
239 }
240
241 finalizeHdr(*this);
242}

244void Mat::copySize(const Mat& m)
245{
246 setSize(*this, m.dims, 0, 0);
247 for( int i = 0; i < dims; i++ )
248 {
249 size[i] = m.size[i];
250 step[i] = m.step[i];
251 }
252}
253
254void Mat::deallocate()
255{
256 if( allocator )
257 allocator->deallocate(refcount, datastart, data);
258 else
259 {
260 CV_DbgAssert(refcount != 0);
261 fastFree(datastart);
262 }
263}

266Mat::Mat(const Mat& m, const Range& _rowRange, const Range& _colRange) : size(&rows)
267{
268 initEmpty();
269 CV_Assert( m.dims >= 2 );
270 if( m.dims > 2 )
271 {
272 AutoBuffer<Range> rs(m.dims);
273 rs[0] = _rowRange;
274 rs[1] = _colRange;
275 for( int i = 2; i < m.dims; i++ )
276 rs[i] = Range::all();
277 *this = m(rs);
278 return;
279 }
280
281 *this = m;
282 if( _rowRange != Range::all() && _rowRange != Range(0,rows) )
283 {
284 CV_Assert( 0 <= _rowRange.start && _rowRange.start <= _rowRange.end && _rowRange.end <= m.rows );
285 rows = _rowRange.size();
286 data += step*_rowRange.start;
287 flags |= SUBMATRIX_FLAG;
288 }
289
290 if( _colRange != Range::all() && _colRange != Range(0,cols) )
291 {
292 CV_Assert( 0 <= _colRange.start && _colRange.start <= _colRange.end && _colRange.end <= m.cols );
293 cols = _colRange.size();
294 data += _colRange.start*elemSize();
295 flags &= cols < m.cols ? ~CONTINUOUS_FLAG : -1;
296 flags |= SUBMATRIX_FLAG;
297 }
298
299 if( rows == 1 )
300 flags |= CONTINUOUS_FLAG;
301
302 if( rows <= 0 || cols <= 0 )
303 {
304 release();
305 rows = cols = 0;
306 }
307}

310Mat::Mat(const Mat& m, const Rect& roi)
311 : flags(m.flags), dims(2), rows(roi.height), cols(roi.width),
312 data(m.data + roi.y*m.step[0]), refcount(m.refcount),
313 datastart(m.datastart), dataend(m.dataend), datalimit(m.datalimit),
314 allocator(m.allocator), size(&rows)
315{
316 CV_Assert( m.dims <= 2 );
317 flags &= roi.width < m.cols ? ~CONTINUOUS_FLAG : -1;
318 flags |= roi.height == 1 ? CONTINUOUS_FLAG : 0;
319
320 size_t esz = CV_ELEM_SIZE(flags);
321 data += roi.x*esz;
322 CV_Assert( 0 <= roi.x && 0 <= roi.width && roi.x + roi.width <= m.cols &&
323 0 <= roi.y && 0 <= roi.height && roi.y + roi.height <= m.rows );
324 if( refcount )
325 CV_XADD(refcount, 1);
326 if( roi.width < m.cols || roi.height < m.rows )
327 flags |= SUBMATRIX_FLAG;
328
329 step[0] = m.step[0]; step[1] = esz;
330
331 if( rows <= 0 || cols <= 0 )
332 {
333 release();
334 rows = cols = 0;
335 }
336}

339Mat::Mat(int _dims, const int* _sizes, int _type, void* _data, const size_t* _steps) : size(&rows)
340{
341 initEmpty();
342 flags |= CV_MAT_TYPE(_type);
343 data = datastart = (uchar*)_data;
344 setSize(*this, _dims, _sizes, _steps, true);
345 finalizeHdr(*this);
346}

348
349Mat::Mat(const Mat& m, const Range* ranges) : size(&rows)
350{
351 initEmpty();
352 int i, d = m.dims;
353
354 CV_Assert(ranges);
355 for( i = 0; i < d; i++ )
356 {
357 Range r = ranges[i];
358 CV_Assert( r == Range::all() || (0 <= r.start && r.start < r.end && r.end <= m.size[i]) );
359 }
360 *this = m;
361 for( i = 0; i < d; i++ )
362 {
363 Range r = ranges[i];
364 if( r != Range::all() && r != Range(0, size.p[i]))
365 {
366 size.p[i] = r.end - r.start;
367 data += r.start*step.p[i];
368 flags |= SUBMATRIX_FLAG;
369 }
370 }
371 updateContinuityFlag(*this);
372}

375Mat::Mat(const CvMatND* m, bool copyData) : size(&rows)
376{
377 initEmpty();
378 if( !m )
379 return;
380 data = datastart = m->data.ptr;
381 flags |= CV_MAT_TYPE(m->type);
382 int _sizes[CV_MAX_DIM];
383 size_t _steps[CV_MAX_DIM];
384
385 int i, d = m->dims;
386 for( i = 0; i < d; i++ )
387 {
388 _sizes[i] = m->dim[i].size;
389 _steps[i] = m->dim[i].step;
390 }
391
392 setSize(*this, d, _sizes, _steps);
393 finalizeHdr(*this);
394
395 if( copyData )
396 {
397 Mat temp(*this);
398 temp.copyTo(*this);
399 }
400}

402
403Mat Mat::diag(int d) const
404{
405 CV_Assert( dims <= 2 );
406 Mat m = *this;
407 size_t esz = elemSize();
408 int len;
409
410 if( d >= 0 )
411 {
412 len = std::min(cols - d, rows);
413 m.data += esz*d;
414 }
415 else
416 {
417 len = std::min(rows + d, cols);
418 m.data -= step[0]*d;
419 }
420 CV_DbgAssert( len > 0 );
421
422 m.size[0] = m.rows = len;
423 m.size[1] = m.cols = 1;
424 m.step[0] += (len > 1 ? esz : 0);
425
426 if( m.rows > 1 )
427 m.flags &= ~CONTINUOUS_FLAG;
428 else
429 m.flags |= CONTINUOUS_FLAG;
430
431 if( size() != Size(1,1) )
432 m.flags |= SUBMATRIX_FLAG;
433
434 return m;
435}

437
438Mat::Mat(const CvMat* m, bool copyData) : size(&rows)
439{
440 initEmpty();
441
442 if( !m )
443 return;
444
445 if( !copyData )
446 {
447 flags = MAGIC_VAL + (m->type & (CV_MAT_TYPE_MASK|CV_MAT_CONT_FLAG));
448 dims = 2;
449 rows = m->rows;
450 cols = m->cols;
451 data = datastart = m->data.ptr;
452 size_t esz = CV_ELEM_SIZE(m->type), minstep = cols*esz, _step = m->step;
453 if( _step == 0 )
454 _step = minstep;
455 datalimit = datastart + _step*rows;
456 dataend = datalimit - _step + minstep;
457 step[0] = _step; step[1] = esz;
458 }
459 else
460 {
461 data = datastart = dataend = 0;
462 Mat(m->rows, m->cols, m->type, m->data.ptr, m->step).copyTo(*this);
463 }
464}

466
467Mat::Mat(const IplImage* img, bool copyData) : size(&rows)
468{
469 initEmpty();
470
471 if( !img )
472 return;
473
474 dims = 2;
475 CV_DbgAssert(CV_IS_IMAGE(img) && img->imageData != 0);
476
477 int imgdepth = IPL2CV_DEPTH(img->depth);
478 size_t esz;
479 step[0] = img->widthStep;
480
481 if(!img->roi)
482 {
483 CV_Assert(img->dataOrder == IPL_DATA_ORDER_PIXEL);
484 flags = MAGIC_VAL + CV_MAKETYPE(imgdepth, img->nChannels);
485 rows = img->height; cols = img->width;
486 datastart = data = (uchar*)img->imageData;
487 esz = CV_ELEM_SIZE(flags);
488 }
489 else
490 {
491 CV_Assert(img->dataOrder == IPL_DATA_ORDER_PIXEL || img->roi->coi != 0);
492 bool selectedPlane = img->roi->coi && img->dataOrder == IPL_DATA_ORDER_PLANE;
493 flags = MAGIC_VAL + CV_MAKETYPE(imgdepth, selectedPlane ? 1 : img->nChannels);
494 rows = img->roi->height; cols = img->roi->width;
495 esz = CV_ELEM_SIZE(flags);
496 data = datastart = (uchar*)img->imageData +
497 (selectedPlane ? (img->roi->coi - 1)*step*img->height : 0) +
498 img->roi->yOffset*step[0] + img->roi->xOffset*esz;
499 }
500 datalimit = datastart + step.p[0]*rows;
501 dataend = datastart + step.p[0]*(rows-1) + esz*cols;
502 flags |= (cols*esz == step.p[0] || rows == 1 ? CONTINUOUS_FLAG : 0);
503 step[1] = esz;
504
505 if( copyData )
506 {
507 Mat m = *this;
508 release();
509 if( !img->roi || !img->roi->coi ||
510 img->dataOrder == IPL_DATA_ORDER_PLANE)
511 m.copyTo(*this);
512 else
513 {
514 int ch[] = {img->roi->coi - 1, 0};
515 create(m.rows, m.cols, m.type());
516 mixChannels(&m, 1, this, 1, ch, 1);
517 }
518 }
519}

522Mat::operator IplImage() const
523{
524 CV_Assert( dims <= 2 );
525 IplImage img;
526 cvInitImageHeader(&img, size(), cvIplDepth(flags), channels());
527 cvSetData(&img, data, (int)step[0]);
528 return img;
529}

532void Mat::pop_back(size_t nelems)
533{
534 CV_Assert( nelems <= (size_t)size.p[0] );
535
536 if( isSubmatrix() )
537 *this = rowRange(0, size.p[0] - (int)nelems);
538 else
539 {
540 size.p[0] -= (int)nelems;
541 dataend -= nelems*step.p[0];
542 /*if( size.p[0] <= 1 )
543 {
544 if( dims <= 2 )
545 flags |= CONTINUOUS_FLAG;
546 else
547 updateContinuityFlag(*this);
548 }*/
549 }
550}
551
552
553void Mat::push_back_(const void* elem)
554{
555 int r = size.p[0];
556 if( isSubmatrix() || dataend + step.p[0] > datalimit )
557 reserve( std::max(r + 1, (r*3+1)/2) );
558
559 size_t esz = elemSize();
560 memcpy(data + r*step.p[0], elem, esz);
561 size.p[0] = r + 1;
562 dataend += step.p[0];
563 if( esz < step.p[0] )
564 flags &= ~CONTINUOUS_FLAG;
565}
566
567void Mat::reserve(size_t nelems)
568{
569 const size_t MIN_SIZE = 64;
570
571 CV_Assert( (int)nelems >= 0 );
572 if( !isSubmatrix() && data + step.p[0]*nelems <= datalimit )
573 return;
574
575 int r = size.p[0];
576
577 if( (size_t)r >= nelems )
578 return;
579
580 size.p[0] = std::max((int)nelems, 1);
581 size_t newsize = total()*elemSize();
582
583 if( newsize < MIN_SIZE )
584 size.p[0] = (int)((MIN_SIZE + newsize - 1)*nelems/newsize);
585
586 Mat m(dims, size.p, type());
587 size.p[0] = r;
588 if( r > 0 )
589 {
590 Mat mpart = m.rowRange(0, r);
591 copyTo(mpart);
592 }
593
594 *this = m;
595 size.p[0] = r;
596 dataend = data + step.p[0]*r;
597}

599
600void Mat::resize(size_t nelems)
601{
602 int saveRows = size.p[0];
603 if( saveRows == (int)nelems )
604 return;
605 CV_Assert( (int)nelems >= 0 );
606
607 if( isSubmatrix() || data + step.p[0]*nelems > datalimit )
608 reserve(nelems);
609
610 size.p[0] = (int)nelems;
611 dataend += (size.p[0] - saveRows)*step.p[0];
612
613 //updateContinuityFlag(*this);
614}

616
617void Mat::resize(size_t nelems, const Scalar& s)
618{
619 int saveRows = size.p[0];
620 resize(nelems);
621
622 if( size.p[0] > saveRows )
623 {
624 Mat part = rowRange(saveRows, size.p[0]);
625 part = s;
626 }
627}
628
629void Mat::push_back(const Mat& elems)
630{
631 int r = size.p[0], delta = elems.size.p[0];
632 if( delta == 0 )
633 return;
634 if( this == &elems )
635 {
636 Mat tmp = elems;
637 push_back(tmp);
638 return;
639 }
640 if( !data )
641 {
642 *this = elems.clone();
643 return;
644 }
645
646 size.p[0] = elems.size.p[0];
647 bool eq = size == elems.size;
648 size.p[0] = r;
649 if( !eq )
650 CV_Error(CV_StsUnmatchedSizes, "");
651 if( type() != elems.type() )
652 CV_Error(CV_StsUnmatchedFormats, "");
653
654 if( isSubmatrix() || dataend + step.p[0]*delta > datalimit )
655 reserve( std::max(r + delta, (r*3+1)/2) );
656
657 size.p[0] += delta;
658 dataend += step.p[0]*delta;
659
660 //updateContinuityFlag(*this);
661
662 if( isContinuous() && elems.isContinuous() )
663 memcpy(data + r*step.p[0], elems.data, elems.total()*elems.elemSize());
664 else
665 {
666 Mat part = rowRange(r, r + delta);
667 elems.copyTo(part);
668 }
669}

671
672Mat cvarrToMat(const CvArr* arr, bool copyData,
673 bool /*allowND*/, int coiMode)
674{
675 if( !arr )
676 return Mat();
677 if( CV_IS_MAT(arr) )
678 return Mat((const CvMat*)arr, copyData );
679 if( CV_IS_MATND(arr) )
680 return Mat((const CvMatND*)arr, copyData );
681 if( CV_IS_IMAGE(arr) )
682 {
683 const IplImage* iplimg = (const IplImage*)arr;
684 if( coiMode == 0 && iplimg->roi && iplimg->roi->coi > 0 )
685 CV_Error(CV_BadCOI, "COI is not supported by the function");
686 return Mat(iplimg, copyData);
687 }
688 if( CV_IS_SEQ(arr) )
689 {
690 CvSeq* seq = (CvSeq*)arr;
691 CV_Assert(seq->total > 0 && CV_ELEM_SIZE(seq->flags) == seq->elem_size);
692 if(!copyData && seq->first->next == seq->first)
693 return Mat(seq->total, 1, CV_MAT_TYPE(seq->flags), seq->first->data);
694 Mat buf(seq->total, 1, CV_MAT_TYPE(seq->flags));
695 cvCvtSeqToArray(seq, buf.data, CV_WHOLE_SEQ);
696 return buf;
697 }
698 CV_Error(CV_StsBadArg, "Unknown array type");
699 return Mat();
700}
701
702void Mat::locateROI( Size& wholeSize, Point& ofs ) const
703{
704 CV_Assert( dims <= 2 && step[0] > 0 );
705 size_t esz = elemSize(), minstep;
706 ptrdiff_t delta1 = data - datastart, delta2 = dataend - datastart;
707
708 if( delta1 == 0 )
709 ofs.x = ofs.y = 0;
710 else
711 {
712 ofs.y = (int)(delta1/step[0]);
713 ofs.x = (int)((delta1 - step[0]*ofs.y)/esz);
714 CV_DbgAssert( data == datastart + ofs.y*step[0] + ofs.x*esz );
715 }
716 minstep = (ofs.x + cols)*esz;
717 wholeSize.height = (int)((delta2 - minstep)/step[0] + 1);
718 wholeSize.height = std::max(wholeSize.height, ofs.y + rows);
719 wholeSize.width = (int)((delta2 - step*(wholeSize.height-1))/esz);
720 wholeSize.width = std::max(wholeSize.width, ofs.x + cols);
721}
722
723Mat& Mat::adjustROI( int dtop, int dbottom, int dleft, int dright )
724{
725 CV_Assert( dims <= 2 && step[0] > 0 );
726 Size wholeSize; Point ofs;
727 size_t esz = elemSize();
728 locateROI( wholeSize, ofs );
729 int row1 = std::max(ofs.y - dtop, 0), row2 = std::min(ofs.y + rows + dbottom, wholeSize.height);
730 int col1 = std::max(ofs.x - dleft, 0), col2 = std::min(ofs.x + cols + dright, wholeSize.width);
731 data += (row1 - ofs.y)*step + (col1 - ofs.x)*esz;
732 rows = row2 - row1; cols = col2 - col1;
733 size.p[0] = rows; size.p[1] = cols;
734 if( esz*cols == step[0] || rows == 1 )
735 flags |= CONTINUOUS_FLAG;
736 else
737 flags &= ~CONTINUOUS_FLAG;
738 return *this;
739}
740
741}
742
743void cv::extractImageCOI(const CvArr* arr, OutputArray _ch, int coi)
744{
745 Mat mat = cvarrToMat(arr, false, true, 1);
746 _ch.create(mat.dims, mat.size, mat.depth());
747 Mat ch = _ch.getMat();
748 if(coi < 0)
749 {
750 CV_Assert( CV_IS_IMAGE(arr) );
751 coi = cvGetImageCOI((const IplImage*)arr)-1;
752 }
753 CV_Assert(0 <= coi && coi < mat.channels());
754 int _pairs[] = { coi, 0 };
755 mixChannels( &mat, 1, &ch, 1, _pairs, 1 );
756}
757
758void cv::insertImageCOI(InputArray _ch, CvArr* arr, int coi)
759{
760 Mat ch = _ch.getMat(), mat = cvarrToMat(arr, false, true, 1);
761 if(coi < 0)
762 {
763 CV_Assert( CV_IS_IMAGE(arr) );
764 coi = cvGetImageCOI((const IplImage*)arr)-1;
765 }
766 CV_Assert(ch.size == mat.size && ch.depth() == mat.depth() && 0 <= coi && coi < mat.channels());
767 int _pairs[] = { 0, coi };
768 mixChannels( &ch, 1, &mat, 1, _pairs, 1 );
769}

773
774Mat Mat::reshape(int new_cn, int new_rows) const
775{
776 int cn = channels();
777 Mat hdr = *this;
778
779 if( dims > 2 && new_rows == 0 && new_cn != 0 && size[dims-1]*cn % new_cn == 0 )
780 {
781 hdr.flags = (hdr.flags & ~CV_MAT_CN_MASK) | ((new_cn-1) << CV_CN_SHIFT);
782 hdr.step[dims-1] = CV_ELEM_SIZE(hdr.flags);
783 hdr.size[dims-1] = hdr.size[dims-1]*cn / new_cn;
784 return hdr;
785 }
786
787 CV_Assert( dims <= 2 );
788
789 if( new_cn == 0 )
790 new_cn = cn;
791
792 int total_width = cols * cn;
793
794 if( (new_cn > total_width || total_width % new_cn != 0) && new_rows == 0 )
795 new_rows = rows * total_width / new_cn;
796
797 if( new_rows != 0 && new_rows != rows )
798 {
799 int total_size = total_width * rows;
800 if( !isContinuous() )
801 CV_Error( CV_BadStep,
802 "The matrix is not continuous, thus its number of rows can not be changed" );
803
804 if( (unsigned)new_rows > (unsigned)total_size )
805 CV_Error( CV_StsOutOfRange, "Bad new number of rows" );
806
807 total_width = total_size / new_rows;
808
809 if( total_width * new_rows != total_size )
810 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "The total number of matrix elements "
811 "is not divisible by the new number of rows" );
812
813 hdr.rows = new_rows;
814 hdr.step[0] = total_width * elemSize1();
815 }
816
817 int new_width = total_width / new_cn;
818
819 if( new_width * new_cn != total_width )
820 CV_Error( CV_BadNumChannels,
821 "The total width is not divisible by the new number of channels" );
822
823 hdr.cols = new_width;
824 hdr.flags = (hdr.flags & ~CV_MAT_CN_MASK) | ((new_cn-1) << CV_CN_SHIFT);
825 hdr.step[1] = CV_ELEM_SIZE(hdr.flags);
826 return hdr;
827}

829
830int Mat::checkVector(int _elemChannels, int _depth, bool _requireContinuous) const
831{
832 return (depth() == _depth || _depth <= 0) &&
833 (isContinuous() || !_requireContinuous) &&
834 ((dims == 2 && (((rows == 1 || cols == 1) && channels() == _elemChannels) ||
835 (cols == _elemChannels && channels() == 1))) ||
836 (dims == 3 && channels() == 1 && size.p[2] == _elemChannels && (size.p[0] == 1 || size.p[1] == 1) &&
837 (isContinuous() || step.p[1] == step.p[2]*size.p[2])))
838 ? (int)(total()*channels()/_elemChannels) : -1;
839}

841
842void scalarToRawData(const Scalar& s, void* _buf, int type, int unroll_to)
843{
844 int i, depth = CV_MAT_DEPTH(type), cn = CV_MAT_CN(type);
845 CV_Assert(cn <= 4);
846 switch(depth)
847 {
848 case CV_8U:
849 {
850 uchar* buf = (uchar*)_buf;
851 for(i = 0; i < cn; i++)
852 buf[i] = saturate_cast<uchar>(s.val[i]);
853 for(; i < unroll_to; i++)
854 buf[i] = buf[i-cn];
855 }
856 break;
857 case CV_8S:
858 {
859 schar* buf = (schar*)_buf;
860 for(i = 0; i < cn; i++)
861 buf[i] = saturate_cast<schar>(s.val[i]);
862 for(; i < unroll_to; i++)
863 buf[i] = buf[i-cn];
864 }
865 break;
866 case CV_16U:
867 {
868 ushort* buf = (ushort*)_buf;
869 for(i = 0; i < cn; i++)
870 buf[i] = saturate_cast<ushort>(s.val[i]);
871 for(; i < unroll_to; i++)
872 buf[i] = buf[i-cn];
873 }
874 break;
875 case CV_16S:
876 {
877 short* buf = (short*)_buf;
878 for(i = 0; i < cn; i++)
879 buf[i] = saturate_cast<short>(s.val[i]);
880 for(; i < unroll_to; i++)
881 buf[i] = buf[i-cn];
882 }
883 break;
884 case CV_32S:
885 {
886 int* buf = (int*)_buf;
887 for(i = 0; i < cn; i++)
888 buf[i] = saturate_cast<int>(s.val[i]);
889 for(; i < unroll_to; i++)
890 buf[i] = buf[i-cn];
891 }
892 break;
893 case CV_32F:
894 {
895 float* buf = (float*)_buf;
896 for(i = 0; i < cn; i++)
897 buf[i] = saturate_cast<float>(s.val[i]);
898 for(; i < unroll_to; i++)
899 buf[i] = buf[i-cn];
900 }
901 break;
902 case CV_64F:
903 {
904 double* buf = (double*)_buf;
905 for(i = 0; i < cn; i++)
906 buf[i] = saturate_cast<double>(s.val[i]);
907 for(; i < unroll_to; i++)
908 buf[i] = buf[i-cn];
909 break;
910 }
911 default:
912 CV_Error(CV_StsUnsupportedFormat,"");
913 }
914}

937Mat _InputArray::getMat(int i) const
938{
939 int k = kind();
940
941 if( k == MAT )
942 {
943 const Mat* m = (const Mat*)obj;
944 if( i < 0 )
945 return *m;
946 return m->row(i);
947 }
948
949 if( k == EXPR )
950 {
951 CV_Assert( i < 0 );
952 return (Mat)*((const MatExpr*)obj);
953 }
954
955 if( k == MATX )
956 {
957 CV_Assert( i < 0 );
958 return Mat(sz, flags, obj);
959 }
960
961 if( k == STD_VECTOR )
962 {
963 CV_Assert( i < 0 );
964 int t = CV_MAT_TYPE(flags);
965 const vector<uchar>& v = *(const vector<uchar>*)obj;
966
967 return !v.empty() ? Mat(size(), t, (void*)&v[0]) : Mat();
968 }
969
970 if( k == NONE )
971 return Mat();
972
973 if( k == STD_VECTOR_VECTOR )
974 {
975 int t = type(i);
976 const vector<vector<uchar> >& vv = *(const vector<vector<uchar> >*)obj;
977 CV_Assert( 0 <= i && i < (int)vv.size() );
978 const vector<uchar>& v = vv[i];
979
980 return !v.empty() ? Mat(size(i), t, (void*)&v[0]) : Mat();
981 }
982
983 if( k == OCL_MAT )
984 {
985 CV_Error(CV_StsNotImplemented, "This method is not implemented for oclMat yet");
986 }
987
988 CV_Assert( k == STD_VECTOR_MAT );
989 //if( k == STD_VECTOR_MAT )
990 {
991 const vector<Mat>& v = *(const vector<Mat>*)obj;
992 CV_Assert( 0 <= i && i < (int)v.size() );
993
994 return v[i];
995 }
996}

999void _InputArray::getMatVector(vector<Mat>& mv) const
1000{
1001 int k = kind();
1002
1003 if( k == MAT )
1004 {
1005 const Mat& m = *(const Mat*)obj;
1006 int i, n = (int)m.size[0];
1007 mv.resize(n);
1008
1009 for( i = 0; i < n; i++ )
1010 mv[i] = m.dims == 2 ? Mat(1, m.cols, m.type(), (void*)m.ptr(i)) :
1011 Mat(m.dims-1, &m.size[1], m.type(), (void*)m.ptr(i), &m.step[1]);
1012 return;
1013 }
1014
1015 if( k == EXPR )
1016 {
1017 Mat m = *(const MatExpr*)obj;
1018 int i, n = m.size[0];
1019 mv.resize(n);
1020
1021 for( i = 0; i < n; i++ )
1022 mv[i] = m.row(i);
1023 return;
1024 }
1025
1026 if( k == MATX )
1027 {
1028 size_t i, n = sz.height, esz = CV_ELEM_SIZE(flags);
1029 mv.resize(n);
1030
1031 for( i = 0; i < n; i++ )
1032 mv[i] = Mat(1, sz.width, CV_MAT_TYPE(flags), (uchar*)obj + esz*sz.width*i);
1033 return;
1034 }
1035
1036 if( k == STD_VECTOR )
1037 {
1038 const vector<uchar>& v = *(const vector<uchar>*)obj;
1039
1040 size_t i, n = v.size(), esz = CV_ELEM_SIZE(flags);
1041 int t = CV_MAT_DEPTH(flags), cn = CV_MAT_CN(flags);
1042 mv.resize(n);
1043
1044 for( i = 0; i < n; i++ )
1045 mv[i] = Mat(1, cn, t, (void*)(&v[0] + esz*i));
1046 return;
1047 }
1048
1049 if( k == NONE )
1050 {
1051 mv.clear();
1052 return;
1053 }
1054
1055 if( k == STD_VECTOR_VECTOR )
1056 {
1057 const vector<vector<uchar> >& vv = *(const vector<vector<uchar> >*)obj;
1058 int i, n = (int)vv.size();
1059 int t = CV_MAT_TYPE(flags);
1060 mv.resize(n);
1061
1062 for( i = 0; i < n; i++ )
1063 {
1064 const vector<uchar>& v = vv[i];
1065 mv[i] = Mat(size(i), t, (void*)&v[0]);
1066 }
1067 return;
1068 }
1069
1070 if( k == OCL_MAT )
1071 {
1072 CV_Error(CV_StsNotImplemented, "This method is not implemented for oclMat yet");
1073 }
1074
1075 CV_Assert( k == STD_VECTOR_MAT );
1076 //if( k == STD_VECTOR_MAT )
1077 {
1078 const vector<Mat>& v = *(const vector<Mat>*)obj;
1079 mv.resize(v.size());
1080 std::copy(v.begin(), v.end(), mv.begin());
1081 return;
1082 }

1132Size _InputArray::size(int i) const
1133{
1134 int k = kind();
1135
1136 if( k == MAT )
1137 {
1138 CV_Assert( i < 0 );
1139 return ((const Mat*)obj)->size();
1140 }
1141
1142 if( k == EXPR )
1143 {
1144 CV_Assert( i < 0 );
1145 return ((const MatExpr*)obj)->size();
1146 }
1147
1148 if( k == MATX )
1149 {
1150 CV_Assert( i < 0 );
1151 return sz;
1152 }
1153
1154 if( k == STD_VECTOR )
1155 {
1156 CV_Assert( i < 0 );
1157 const vector<uchar>& v = *(const vector<uchar>*)obj;
1158 const vector<int>& iv = *(const vector<int>*)obj;
1159 size_t szb = v.size(), szi = iv.size();
1160 return szb == szi ? Size((int)szb, 1) : Size((int)(szb/CV_ELEM_SIZE(flags)), 1);
1161 }
1162
1163 if( k == NONE )
1164 return Size();
1165
1166 if( k == STD_VECTOR_VECTOR )
1167 {
1168 const vector<vector<uchar> >& vv = *(const vector<vector<uchar> >*)obj;
1169 if( i < 0 )
1170 return vv.empty() ? Size() : Size((int)vv.size(), 1);
1171 CV_Assert( i < (int)vv.size() );
1172 const vector<vector<int> >& ivv = *(const vector<vector<int> >*)obj;
1173
1174 size_t szb = vv[i].size(), szi = ivv[i].size();
1175 return szb == szi ? Size((int)szb, 1) : Size((int)(szb/CV_ELEM_SIZE(flags)), 1);
1176 }
1177
1178 if( k == STD_VECTOR_MAT )
1179 {
1180 const vector<Mat>& vv = *(const vector<Mat>*)obj;
1181 if( i < 0 )
1182 return vv.empty() ? Size() : Size((int)vv.size(), 1);
1183 CV_Assert( i < (int)vv.size() );
1184
1185 return vv[i].size();
1186 }
1187
1188 if( k == OPENGL_BUFFER )
1189 {
1190 CV_Assert( i < 0 );
1191 const ogl::Buffer* buf = (const ogl::Buffer*)obj;
1192 return buf->size();
1193 }
1194
1195 if( k == OPENGL_TEXTURE )
1196 {
1197 CV_Assert( i < 0 );
1198 const ogl::Texture2D* tex = (const ogl::Texture2D*)obj;
1199 return tex->size();
1200 }
1201
1202 if( k == OCL_MAT )
1203 {
1204 CV_Error(CV_StsNotImplemented, "This method is not implemented for oclMat yet");
1205 }
1206
1207 CV_Assert( k == GPU_MAT );
1208 //if( k == GPU_MAT )
1209 {
1210 CV_Assert( i < 0 );
1211 const gpu::GpuMat* d_mat = (const gpu::GpuMat*)obj;
1212 return d_mat->size();
1213 }

1359void _OutputArray::create(Size _sz, int mtype, int i, bool allowTransposed, int fixedDepthMask) const
1360{
1361 int k = kind();
1362 if( k == MAT && i < 0 && !allowTransposed && fixedDepthMask == 0 )
1363 {
1364 CV_Assert(!fixedSize() || ((Mat*)obj)->size.operator()() == _sz);
1365 CV_Assert(!fixedType() || ((Mat*)obj)->type() == mtype);
1366 ((Mat*)obj)->create(_sz, mtype);
1367 return;
1368 }
1369 if( k == GPU_MAT && i < 0 && !allowTransposed && fixedDepthMask == 0 )
1370 {
1371 CV_Assert(!fixedSize() || ((gpu::GpuMat*)obj)->size() == _sz);
1372 CV_Assert(!fixedType() || ((gpu::GpuMat*)obj)->type() == mtype);
1373 ((gpu::GpuMat*)obj)->create(_sz, mtype);
1374 return;
1375 }
1376 if( k == OPENGL_BUFFER && i < 0 && !allowTransposed && fixedDepthMask == 0 )
1377 {
1378 CV_Assert(!fixedSize() || ((ogl::Buffer*)obj)->size() == _sz);
1379 CV_Assert(!fixedType() || ((ogl::Buffer*)obj)->type() == mtype);
1380 ((ogl::Buffer*)obj)->create(_sz, mtype);
1381 return;
1382 }
1383 int sizes[] = {_sz.height, _sz.width};
1384 create(2, sizes, mtype, i, allowTransposed, fixedDepthMask);
1385}

1387void _OutputArray::create(int rows, int cols, int mtype, int i, bool allowTransposed, int fixedDepthMask) const
1388{
1389 int k = kind();
1390 if( k == MAT && i < 0 && !allowTransposed && fixedDepthMask == 0 )
1391 {
1392 CV_Assert(!fixedSize() || ((Mat*)obj)->size.operator()() == Size(cols, rows));
1393 CV_Assert(!fixedType() || ((Mat*)obj)->type() == mtype);
1394 ((Mat*)obj)->create(rows, cols, mtype);
1395 return;
1396 }
1397 if( k == GPU_MAT && i < 0 && !allowTransposed && fixedDepthMask == 0 )
1398 {
1399 CV_Assert(!fixedSize() || ((gpu::GpuMat*)obj)->size() == Size(cols, rows));
1400 CV_Assert(!fixedType() || ((gpu::GpuMat*)obj)->type() == mtype);
1401 ((gpu::GpuMat*)obj)->create(rows, cols, mtype);
1402 return;
1403 }
1404 if( k == OPENGL_BUFFER && i < 0 && !allowTransposed && fixedDepthMask == 0 )
1405 {
1406 CV_Assert(!fixedSize() || ((ogl::Buffer*)obj)->size() == Size(cols, rows));
1407 CV_Assert(!fixedType() || ((ogl::Buffer*)obj)->type() == mtype);
1408 ((ogl::Buffer*)obj)->create(rows, cols, mtype);
1409 return;
1410 }
1411 int sizes[] = {rows, cols};
1412 create(2, sizes, mtype, i, allowTransposed, fixedDepthMask);
1413}
1414
1415void _OutputArray::create(int dims, const int* sizes, int mtype, int i, bool allowTransposed, int fixedDepthMask) const
1416{
1417 int k = kind();
1418 mtype = CV_MAT_TYPE(mtype);
1419
1420 if( k == MAT )
1421 {
1422 CV_Assert( i < 0 );
1423 Mat& m = *(Mat*)obj;
1424 if( allowTransposed )
1425 {
1426 if( !m.isContinuous() )
1427 {
1428 CV_Assert(!fixedType() && !fixedSize());
1429 m.release();
1430 }
1431
1432 if( dims == 2 && m.dims == 2 && m.data &&
1433 m.type() == mtype && m.rows == sizes[1] && m.cols == sizes[0] )
1434 return;
1435 }
1436
1437 if(fixedType())
1438 {
1439 if(CV_MAT_CN(mtype) == m.channels() && ((1 << CV_MAT_TYPE(flags)) & fixedDepthMask) != 0 )
1440 mtype = m.type();
1441 else
1442 CV_Assert(CV_MAT_TYPE(mtype) == m.type());
1443 }
1444 if(fixedSize())
1445 {
1446 CV_Assert(m.dims == dims);
1447 for(int j = 0; j < dims; ++j)
1448 CV_Assert(m.size[j] == sizes[j]);
1449 }
1450 m.create(dims, sizes, mtype);
1451 return;
1452 }
1453
1454 if( k == MATX )
1455 {
1456 CV_Assert( i < 0 );
1457 int type0 = CV_MAT_TYPE(flags);
1458 CV_Assert( mtype == type0 || (CV_MAT_CN(mtype) == 1 && ((1 << type0) & fixedDepthMask) != 0) );
1459 CV_Assert( dims == 2 && ((sizes[0] == sz.height && sizes[1] == sz.width) ||
1460 (allowTransposed && sizes[0] == sz.width && sizes[1] == sz.height)));
1461 return;
1462 }
1463
1464 if( k == STD_VECTOR || k == STD_VECTOR_VECTOR )
1465 {
1466 CV_Assert( dims == 2 && (sizes[0] == 1 || sizes[1] == 1 || sizes[0]*sizes[1] == 0) );
1467 size_t len = sizes[0]*sizes[1] > 0 ? sizes[0] + sizes[1] - 1 : 0;
1468 vector<uchar>* v = (vector<uchar>*)obj;
1469
1470 if( k == STD_VECTOR_VECTOR )
1471 {
1472 vector<vector<uchar> >& vv = *(vector<vector<uchar> >*)obj;
1473 if( i < 0 )
1474 {
1475 CV_Assert(!fixedSize() || len == vv.size());
1476 vv.resize(len);
1477 return;
1478 }
1479 CV_Assert( i < (int)vv.size() );
1480 v = &vv[i];
1481 }
1482 else
1483 CV_Assert( i < 0 );
1484
1485 int type0 = CV_MAT_TYPE(flags);
1486 CV_Assert( mtype == type0 || (CV_MAT_CN(mtype) == CV_MAT_CN(type0) && ((1 << type0) & fixedDepthMask) != 0) );
1487
1488 int esz = CV_ELEM_SIZE(type0);
1489 CV_Assert(!fixedSize() || len == ((vector<uchar>*)v)->size() / esz);
1490 switch( esz )
1491 {
1492 case 1:
1493 ((vector<uchar>*)v)->resize(len);
1494 break;
1495 case 2:
1496 ((vector<Vec2b>*)v)->resize(len);
1497 break;
1498 case 3:
1499 ((vector<Vec3b>*)v)->resize(len);
1500 break;
1501 case 4:
1502 ((vector<int>*)v)->resize(len);
1503 break;
1504 case 6:
1505 ((vector<Vec3s>*)v)->resize(len);
1506 break;
1507 case 8:
1508 ((vector<Vec2i>*)v)->resize(len);
1509 break;
1510 case 12:
1511 ((vector<Vec3i>*)v)->resize(len);
1512 break;
1513 case 16:
1514 ((vector<Vec4i>*)v)->resize(len);
1515 break;
1516 case 24:
1517 ((vector<Vec6i>*)v)->resize(len);
1518 break;
1519 case 32:
1520 ((vector<Vec8i>*)v)->resize(len);
1521 break;
1522 case 36:
1523 ((vector<Vec<int, 9> >*)v)->resize(len);
1524 break;
1525 case 48:
1526 ((vector<Vec<int, 12> >*)v)->resize(len);
1527 break;
1528 case 64:
1529 ((vector<Vec<int, 16> >*)v)->resize(len);
1530 break;
1531 case 128:
1532 ((vector<Vec<int, 32> >*)v)->resize(len);
1533 break;
1534 case 256:
1535 ((vector<Vec<int, 64> >*)v)->resize(len);
1536 break;
1537 case 512:
1538 ((vector<Vec<int, 128> >*)v)->resize(len);
1539 break;
1540 default:
1541 CV_Error_(CV_StsBadArg, ("Vectors with element size %d are not supported. Please, modify OutputArray::create()\n", esz));
1542 }
1543 return;
1544 }
1545
1546 if( k == OCL_MAT )
1547 {
1548 CV_Error(CV_StsNotImplemented, "This method is not implemented for oclMat yet");
1549 }
1550
1551 if( k == NONE )
1552 {
1553 CV_Error(CV_StsNullPtr, "create() called for the missing output array" );
1554 return;
1555 }
1556
1557 CV_Assert( k == STD_VECTOR_MAT );
1558 //if( k == STD_VECTOR_MAT )
1559 {
1560 vector<Mat>& v = *(vector<Mat>*)obj;
1561
1562 if( i < 0 )
1563 {
1564 CV_Assert( dims == 2 && (sizes[0] == 1 || sizes[1] == 1 || sizes[0]*sizes[1] == 0) );
1565 size_t len = sizes[0]*sizes[1] > 0 ? sizes[0] + sizes[1] - 1 : 0, len0 = v.size();
1566
1567 CV_Assert(!fixedSize() || len == len0);
1568 v.resize(len);
1569 if( fixedType() )
1570 {
1571 int _type = CV_MAT_TYPE(flags);
1572 for( size_t j = len0; j < len; j++ )
1573 {
1574 if( v[j].type() == _type )
1575 continue;
1576 CV_Assert( v[j].empty() );
1577 v[j].flags = (v[j].flags & ~CV_MAT_TYPE_MASK) | _type;
1578 }
1579 }
1580 return;
1581 }
1582
1583 CV_Assert( i < (int)v.size() );
1584 Mat& m = v[i];
1585
1586 if( allowTransposed )
1587 {
1588 if( !m.isContinuous() )
1589 {
1590 CV_Assert(!fixedType() && !fixedSize());
1591 m.release();
1592 }
1593
1594 if( dims == 2 && m.dims == 2 && m.data &&
1595 m.type() == mtype && m.rows == sizes[1] && m.cols == sizes[0] )
1596 return;
1597 }
1598
1599 if(fixedType())
1600 {
1601 if(CV_MAT_CN(mtype) == m.channels() && ((1 << CV_MAT_TYPE(flags)) & fixedDepthMask) != 0 )
1602 mtype = m.type();
1603 else
1604 CV_Assert(!fixedType() || (CV_MAT_CN(mtype) == m.channels() && ((1 << CV_MAT_TYPE(flags)) & fixedDepthMask) != 0));
1605 }
1606 if(fixedSize())
1607 {
1608 CV_Assert(m.dims == dims);
1609 for(int j = 0; j < dims; ++j)
1610 CV_Assert(m.size[j] == sizes[j]);
1611 }
1612
1613 m.create(dims, sizes, mtype);
1614 }
1615}

1740void cv::hconcat(const Mat* src, size_t nsrc, OutputArray _dst)
1741{
1742 if( nsrc == 0 || !src )
1743 {
1744 _dst.release();
1745 return;
1746 }
1747
1748 int totalCols = 0, cols = 0;
1749 size_t i;
1750 for( i = 0; i < nsrc; i++ )
1751 {
1752 CV_Assert( !src[i].empty() && src[i].dims <= 2 &&
1753 src[i].rows == src[0].rows &&
1754 src[i].type() == src[0].type());
1755 totalCols += src[i].cols;
1756 }
1757 _dst.create( src[0].rows, totalCols, src[0].type());
1758 Mat dst = _dst.getMat();
1759 for( i = 0; i < nsrc; i++ )
1760 {
1761 Mat dpart = dst(Rect(cols, 0, src[i].cols, src[i].rows));
1762 src[i].copyTo(dpart);
1763 cols += src[i].cols;
1764 }
1765}

1820//////////////////////////////////////// set identity ////////////////////////////////////////////
1821void cv::setIdentity( InputOutputArray _m, const Scalar& s )
1822{
1823 Mat m = _m.getMat();
1824 CV_Assert( m.dims <= 2 );
1825 int i, j, rows = m.rows, cols = m.cols, type = m.type();
1826
1827 if( type == CV_32FC1 )
1828 {
1829 float* data = (float*)m.data;
1830 float val = (float)s[0];
1831 size_t step = m.step/sizeof(data[0]);
1832
1833 for( i = 0; i < rows; i++, data += step )
1834 {
1835 for( j = 0; j < cols; j++ )
1836 data[j] = 0;
1837 if( i < cols )
1838 data[i] = val;
1839 }
1840 }
1841 else if( type == CV_64FC1 )
1842 {
1843 double* data = (double*)m.data;
1844 double val = s[0];
1845 size_t step = m.step/sizeof(data[0]);
1846
1847 for( i = 0; i < rows; i++, data += step )
1848 {
1849 for( j = 0; j < cols; j++ )
1850 data[j] = j == i ? val : 0;
1851 }
1852 }
1853 else
1854 {
1855 m = Scalar(0);
1856 m.diag() = s;
1857 }
1858}

1860//////////////////////////////////////////// trace ///////////////////////////////////////////
1861
1862cv::Scalar cv::trace( InputArray _m )
1863{
1864 Mat m = _m.getMat();
1865 CV_Assert( m.dims <= 2 );
1866 int i, type = m.type();
1867 int nm = std::min(m.rows, m.cols);
1868
1869 if( type == CV_32FC1 )
1870 {
1871 const float* ptr = (const float*)m.data;
1872 size_t step = m.step/sizeof(ptr[0]) + 1;
1873 double _s = 0;
1874 for( i = 0; i < nm; i++ )
1875 _s += ptr[i*step];
1876 return _s;
1877 }
1878
1879 if( type == CV_64FC1 )
1880 {
1881 const double* ptr = (const double*)m.data;
1882 size_t step = m.step/sizeof(ptr[0]) + 1;
1883 double _s = 0;
1884 for( i = 0; i < nm; i++ )
1885 _s += ptr[i*step];
1886 return _s;
1887 }
1888
1889 return cv::sum(m.diag());
1890}

1897template<typename T> static void
1898transpose_( const uchar* src, size_t sstep, uchar* dst, size_t dstep, Size sz )
1899{
1900 int i=0, j, m = sz.width, n = sz.height;
1901
1902 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
1903 for(; i <= m - 4; i += 4 )
1904 {
1905 T* d0 = (T*)(dst + dstep*i);
1906 T* d1 = (T*)(dst + dstep*(i+1));
1907 T* d2 = (T*)(dst + dstep*(i+2));
1908 T* d3 = (T*)(dst + dstep*(i+3));
1909
1910 for( j = 0; j <= n - 4; j += 4 )
1911 {
1912 const T* s0 = (const T*)(src + i*sizeof(T) + sstep*j);
1913 const T* s1 = (const T*)(src + i*sizeof(T) + sstep*(j+1));
1914 const T* s2 = (const T*)(src + i*sizeof(T) + sstep*(j+2));
1915 const T* s3 = (const T*)(src + i*sizeof(T) + sstep*(j+3));
1916
1917 d0[j] = s0[0]; d0[j+1] = s1[0]; d0[j+2] = s2[0]; d0[j+3] = s3[0];
1918 d1[j] = s0[1]; d1[j+1] = s1[1]; d1[j+2] = s2[1]; d1[j+3] = s3[1];
1919 d2[j] = s0[2]; d2[j+1] = s1[2]; d2[j+2] = s2[2]; d2[j+3] = s3[2];
1920 d3[j] = s0[3]; d3[j+1] = s1[3]; d3[j+2] = s2[3]; d3[j+3] = s3[3];
1921 }
1922
1923 for( ; j < n; j++ )
1924 {
1925 const T* s0 = (const T*)(src + i*sizeof(T) + j*sstep);
1926 d0[j] = s0[0]; d1[j] = s0[1]; d2[j] = s0[2]; d3[j] = s0[3];
1927 }
1928 }
1929 #endif
1930 for( ; i < m; i++ )
1931 {
1932 T* d0 = (T*)(dst + dstep*i);
1933 j = 0;
1934 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
1935 for(; j <= n - 4; j += 4 )
1936 {
1937 const T* s0 = (const T*)(src + i*sizeof(T) + sstep*j);
1938 const T* s1 = (const T*)(src + i*sizeof(T) + sstep*(j+1));
1939 const T* s2 = (const T*)(src + i*sizeof(T) + sstep*(j+2));
1940 const T* s3 = (const T*)(src + i*sizeof(T) + sstep*(j+3));
1941
1942 d0[j] = s0[0]; d0[j+1] = s1[0]; d0[j+2] = s2[0]; d0[j+3] = s3[0];
1943 }
1944 #endif
1945 for( ; j < n; j++ )
1946 {
1947 const T* s0 = (const T*)(src + i*sizeof(T) + j*sstep);
1948 d0[j] = s0[0];
1949 }
1950 }
1951}
1952
1953template<typename T> static void
1954transposeI_( uchar* data, size_t step, int n )
1955{
1956 int i, j;
1957 for( i = 0; i < n; i++ )
1958 {
1959 T* row = (T*)(data + step*i);
1960 uchar* data1 = data + i*sizeof(T);
1961 for( j = i+1; j < n; j++ )
1962 std::swap( row[j], *(T*)(data1 + step*j) );
1963 }
1964}
1965
1966typedef void (*TransposeFunc)( const uchar* src, size_t sstep, uchar* dst, size_t dstep, Size sz );
1967typedef void (*TransposeInplaceFunc)( uchar* data, size_t step, int n );
1968
1969#define DEF_TRANSPOSE_FUNC(suffix, type) \
1970static void transpose_##suffix( const uchar* src, size_t sstep, uchar* dst, size_t dstep, Size sz ) \
1971{ transpose_<type>(src, sstep, dst, dstep, sz); } \
1972\
1973static void transposeI_##suffix( uchar* data, size_t step, int n ) \
1974{ transposeI_<type>(data, step, n); }
1975
1976DEF_TRANSPOSE_FUNC(8u, uchar)
1977DEF_TRANSPOSE_FUNC(16u, ushort)
1978DEF_TRANSPOSE_FUNC(8uC3, Vec3b)
1979DEF_TRANSPOSE_FUNC(32s, int)
1980DEF_TRANSPOSE_FUNC(16uC3, Vec3s)
1981DEF_TRANSPOSE_FUNC(32sC2, Vec2i)
1982DEF_TRANSPOSE_FUNC(32sC3, Vec3i)
1983DEF_TRANSPOSE_FUNC(32sC4, Vec4i)
1984DEF_TRANSPOSE_FUNC(32sC6, Vec6i)
1985DEF_TRANSPOSE_FUNC(32sC8, Vec8i)
1986
1987static TransposeFunc transposeTab[] =
1988{
1989 0, transpose_8u, transpose_16u, transpose_8uC3, transpose_32s, 0, transpose_16uC3, 0,
1990 transpose_32sC2, 0, 0, 0, transpose_32sC3, 0, 0, 0, transpose_32sC4,
1991 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, transpose_32sC6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, transpose_32sC8
1992};
1993
1994static TransposeInplaceFunc transposeInplaceTab[] =
1995{
1996 0, transposeI_8u, transposeI_16u, transposeI_8uC3, transposeI_32s, 0, transposeI_16uC3, 0,
1997 transposeI_32sC2, 0, 0, 0, transposeI_32sC3, 0, 0, 0, transposeI_32sC4,
1998 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, transposeI_32sC6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, transposeI_32sC8
1999};
2000
2001}
2002
2003void cv::transpose( InputArray _src, OutputArray _dst )
2004{
2005 Mat src = _src.getMat();
2006 size_t esz = src.elemSize();
2007 CV_Assert( src.dims <= 2 && esz <= (size_t)32 );
2008
2009 _dst.create(src.cols, src.rows, src.type());
2010 Mat dst = _dst.getMat();
2011
2012 // handle the case of single-column/single-row matrices, stored in STL vectors.
2013 if( src.rows != dst.cols || src.cols != dst.rows )
2014 {
2015 CV_Assert( src.size() == dst.size() && (src.cols == 1 || src.rows == 1) );
2016 src.copyTo(dst);
2017 return;
2018 }
2019
2020 if( dst.data == src.data )
2021 {
2022 TransposeInplaceFunc func = transposeInplaceTab[esz];
2023 CV_Assert( func != 0 );
2024 func( dst.data, dst.step, dst.rows );
2025 }
2026 else
2027 {
2028 TransposeFunc func = transposeTab[esz];
2029 CV_Assert( func != 0 );
2030 func( src.data, src.step, dst.data, dst.step, src.size() );
2031 }
2032}

2035////////////////////////////////////// completeSymm /////////////////////////////////////////
2036
2037void cv::completeSymm( InputOutputArray _m, bool LtoR )
2038{
2039 Mat m = _m.getMat();
2040 size_t step = m.step, esz = m.elemSize();
2041 CV_Assert( m.dims <= 2 && m.rows == m.cols );
2042
2043 int rows = m.rows;
2044 int j0 = 0, j1 = rows;
2045
2046 uchar* data = m.data;
2047 for( int i = 0; i < rows; i++ )
2048 {
2049 if( !LtoR ) j1 = i; else j0 = i+1;
2050 for( int j = j0; j < j1; j++ )
2051 memcpy(data + (i*step + j*esz), data + (j*step + i*esz), esz);
2052 }
2053}

2055
2056cv::Mat cv::Mat::cross(InputArray _m) const
2057{
2058 Mat m = _m.getMat();
2059 int tp = type(), d = CV_MAT_DEPTH(tp);
2060 CV_Assert( dims <= 2 && m.dims <= 2 && size() == m.size() && tp == m.type() &&
2061 ((rows == 3 && cols == 1) || (cols*channels() == 3 && rows == 1)));
2062 Mat result(rows, cols, tp);
2063
2064 if( d == CV_32F )
2065 {
2066 const float *a = (const float*)data, *b = (const float*)m.data;
2067 float* c = (float*)result.data;
2068 size_t lda = rows > 1 ? step/sizeof(a[0]) : 1;
2069 size_t ldb = rows > 1 ? m.step/sizeof(b[0]) : 1;
2070
2071 c[0] = a[lda] * b[ldb*2] - a[lda*2] * b[ldb];
2072 c[1] = a[lda*2] * b[0] - a[0] * b[ldb*2];
2073 c[2] = a[0] * b[ldb] - a[lda] * b[0];
2074 }
2075 else if( d == CV_64F )
2076 {
2077 const double *a = (const double*)data, *b = (const double*)m.data;
2078 double* c = (double*)result.data;
2079 size_t lda = rows > 1 ? step/sizeof(a[0]) : 1;
2080 size_t ldb = rows > 1 ? m.step/sizeof(b[0]) : 1;
2081
2082 c[0] = a[lda] * b[ldb*2] - a[lda*2] * b[ldb];
2083 c[1] = a[lda*2] * b[0] - a[0] * b[ldb*2];
2084 c[2] = a[0] * b[ldb] - a[lda] * b[0];
2085 }
2086
2087 return result;
2088}

2096template<typename T, typename ST, class Op> static void
2097reduceR_( const Mat& srcmat, Mat& dstmat )
2098{
2099 typedef typename Op::rtype WT;
2100 Size size = srcmat.size();
2101 size.width *= srcmat.channels();
2102 AutoBuffer<WT> buffer(size.width);
2103 WT* buf = buffer;
2104 ST* dst = (ST*)dstmat.data;
2105 const T* src = (const T*)srcmat.data;
2106 size_t srcstep = srcmat.step/sizeof(src[0]);
2107 int i;
2108 Op op;
2109
2110 for( i = 0; i < size.width; i++ )
2111 buf[i] = src[i];
2112
2113 for( ; --size.height; )
2114 {
2115 src += srcstep;
2116 i = 0;
2117 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
2118 for(; i <= size.width - 4; i += 4 )
2119 {
2120 WT s0, s1;
2121 s0 = op(buf[i], (WT)src[i]);
2122 s1 = op(buf[i+1], (WT)src[i+1]);
2123 buf[i] = s0; buf[i+1] = s1;
2124
2125 s0 = op(buf[i+2], (WT)src[i+2]);
2126 s1 = op(buf[i+3], (WT)src[i+3]);
2127 buf[i+2] = s0; buf[i+3] = s1;
2128 }
2129 #endif
2130 for( ; i < size.width; i++ )
2131 buf[i] = op(buf[i], (WT)src[i]);
2132 }
2133
2134 for( i = 0; i < size.width; i++ )
2135 dst[i] = (ST)buf[i];
2136}

2138
2139template<typename T, typename ST, class Op> static void
2140reduceC_( const Mat& srcmat, Mat& dstmat )
2141{
2142 typedef typename Op::rtype WT;
2143 Size size = srcmat.size();
2144 int i, k, cn = srcmat.channels();
2145 size.width *= cn;
2146 Op op;
2147
2148 for( int y = 0; y < size.height; y++ )
2149 {
2150 const T* src = (const T*)(srcmat.data + srcmat.step*y);
2151 ST* dst = (ST*)(dstmat.data + dstmat.step*y);
2152 if( size.width == cn )
2153 for( k = 0; k < cn; k++ )
2154 dst[k] = src[k];
2155 else
2156 {
2157 for( k = 0; k < cn; k++ )
2158 {
2159 WT a0 = src[k], a1 = src[k+cn];
2160 for( i = 2*cn; i <= size.width - 4*cn; i += 4*cn )
2161 {
2162 a0 = op(a0, (WT)src[i+k]);
2163 a1 = op(a1, (WT)src[i+k+cn]);
2164 a0 = op(a0, (WT)src[i+k+cn*2]);
2165 a1 = op(a1, (WT)src[i+k+cn*3]);
2166 }
2167
2168 for( ; i < size.width; i += cn )
2169 {
2170 a0 = op(a0, (WT)src[i+k]);
2171 }
2172 a0 = op(a0, a1);
2173 dst[k] = (ST)a0;
2174 }
2175 }
2176 }
2177}

2179typedef void (*ReduceFunc)( const Mat& src, Mat& dst );

2239 _dst.create(dim == 0 ? 1 : src.rows, dim == 0 ? src.cols : 1,
2240 CV_MAKETYPE(dtype >= 0 ? dtype : stype, cn));
2241 Mat dst = _dst.getMat(), temp = dst;
2242

2315 func = GET_OPTIMIZED(reduceSumC8u32s);

2378
2379template<typename T> static void sort_( const Mat& src, Mat& dst, int flags )
2380{
2381 AutoBuffer<T> buf;
2382 T* bptr;
2383 int i, j, n, len;
2384 bool sortRows = (flags & 1) == CV_SORT_EVERY_ROW;
2385 bool inplace = src.data == dst.data;
2386 bool sortDescending = (flags & CV_SORT_DESCENDING) != 0;
2387
2388 if( sortRows )
2389 n = src.rows, len = src.cols;
2390 else
2391 {
2392 n = src.cols, len = src.rows;
2393 buf.allocate(len);
2394 }
2395 bptr = (T*)buf;
2396
2397 for( i = 0; i < n; i++ )
2398 {
2399 T* ptr = bptr;
2400 if( sortRows )
2401 {
2402 T* dptr = (T*)(dst.data + dst.step*i);
2403 if( !inplace )
2404 {
2405 const T* sptr = (const T*)(src.data + src.step*i);
2406 for( j = 0; j < len; j++ )
2407 dptr[j] = sptr[j];
2408 }
2409 ptr = dptr;
2410 }
2411 else
2412 {
2413 for( j = 0; j < len; j++ )
2414 ptr[j] = ((const T*)(src.data + src.step*j))[i];
2415 }
2416 std::sort( ptr, ptr + len, LessThan<T>() );
2417 if( sortDescending )
2418 for( j = 0; j < len/2; j++ )
2419 std::swap(ptr[j], ptr[len-1-j]);
2420 if( !sortRows )
2421 for( j = 0; j < len; j++ )
2422 ((T*)(dst.data + dst.step*j))[i] = ptr[j];
2423 }
2424}
2425
2426
2427template<typename T> static void sortIdx_( const Mat& src, Mat& dst, int flags )
2428{
2429 AutoBuffer<T> buf;
2430 AutoBuffer<int> ibuf;
2431 T* bptr;
2432 int* _iptr;
2433 int i, j, n, len;
2434 bool sortRows = (flags & 1) == CV_SORT_EVERY_ROW;
2435 bool sortDescending = (flags & CV_SORT_DESCENDING) != 0;
2436
2437 CV_Assert( src.data != dst.data );
2438
2439 if( sortRows )
2440 n = src.rows, len = src.cols;
2441 else
2442 {
2443 n = src.cols, len = src.rows;
2444 buf.allocate(len);
2445 ibuf.allocate(len);
2446 }
2447 bptr = (T*)buf;
2448 _iptr = (int*)ibuf;
2449
2450 for( i = 0; i < n; i++ )
2451 {
2452 T* ptr = bptr;
2453 int* iptr = _iptr;
2454
2455 if( sortRows )
2456 {
2457 ptr = (T*)(src.data + src.step*i);
2458 iptr = (int*)(dst.data + dst.step*i);
2459 }
2460 else
2461 {
2462 for( j = 0; j < len; j++ )
2463 ptr[j] = ((const T*)(src.data + src.step*j))[i];
2464 }
2465 for( j = 0; j < len; j++ )
2466 iptr[j] = j;
2467 std::sort( iptr, iptr + len, LessThanIdx<T>(ptr) );
2468 if( sortDescending )
2469 for( j = 0; j < len/2; j++ )
2470 std::swap(iptr[j], iptr[len-1-j]);
2471 if( !sortRows )
2472 for( j = 0; j < len; j++ )
2473 ((int*)(dst.data + dst.step*j))[i] = iptr[j];
2474 }
2475}

2477typedef void (*SortFunc)(const Mat& src, Mat& dst, int flags);
2478
2479}

2481void cv::sort( InputArray _src, OutputArray _dst, int flags )
2482{
2483 static SortFunc tab[] =
2484 {
2485 sort_<uchar>, sort_<schar>, sort_<ushort>, sort_<short>,
2486 sort_<int>, sort_<float>, sort_<double>, 0
2487 };
2488 Mat src = _src.getMat();
2489 SortFunc func = tab[src.depth()];
2490 CV_Assert( src.dims <= 2 && src.channels() == 1 && func != 0 );
2491 _dst.create( src.size(), src.type() );
2492 Mat dst = _dst.getMat();
2493 func( src, dst, flags );
2494}

2500 sortIdx_<uchar>, sortIdx_<schar>, sortIdx_<ushort>, sortIdx_<short>,
2501 sortIdx_<int>, sortIdx_<float>, sortIdx_<double>, 0

2520
2521static void generateRandomCenter(const vector<Vec2f>& box, float* center, RNG& rng)
2522{
2523 size_t j, dims = box.size();
2524 float margin = 1.f/dims;
2525 for( j = 0; j < dims; j++ )
2526 center[j] = ((float)rng*(1.f+margin*2.f)-margin)*(box[j][1] - box[j][0]) + box[j][0];
2527}
2528
2529class KMeansPPDistanceComputer : public ParallelLoopBody
2530{
2531public:
2532 KMeansPPDistanceComputer( float *_tdist2,
2533 const float *_data,
2534 const float *_dist,
2535 int _dims,
2536 size_t _step,
2537 size_t _stepci )
2538 : tdist2(_tdist2),
2539 data(_data),
2540 dist(_dist),
2541 dims(_dims),
2542 step(_step),
2543 stepci(_stepci) { }
2544
2545 void operator()( const cv::Range& range ) const
2546 {
2547 const int begin = range.start;
2548 const int end = range.end;
2549
2550 for ( int i = begin; i<end; i++ )
2551 {
2552 tdist2[i] = std::min(normL2Sqr_(data + step*i, data + stepci, dims), dist[i]);
2553 }
2554 }
2555
2556private:
2557 KMeansPPDistanceComputer& operator=(const KMeansPPDistanceComputer&); // to quiet MSVC
2558
2559 float *tdist2;
2560 const float *data;
2561 const float *dist;
2562 const int dims;
2563 const size_t step;
2564 const size_t stepci;
2565};
2566
2567/*
2568k-means center initialization using the following algorithm:
2569Arthur & Vassilvitskii (2007) k-means++: The Advantages of Careful Seeding
2570*/
2571static void generateCentersPP(const Mat& _data, Mat& _out_centers,
2572 int K, RNG& rng, int trials)
2573{
2574 int i, j, k, dims = _data.cols, N = _data.rows;
2575 const float* data = _data.ptr<float>(0);
2576 size_t step = _data.step/sizeof(data[0]);
2577 vector<int> _centers(K);
2578 int* centers = &_centers[0];
2579 vector<float> _dist(N*3);
2580 float* dist = &_dist[0], *tdist = dist + N, *tdist2 = tdist + N;
2581 double sum0 = 0;
2582
2583 centers[0] = (unsigned)rng % N;
2584
2585 for( i = 0; i < N; i++ )
2586 {
2587 dist[i] = normL2Sqr_(data + step*i, data + step*centers[0], dims);
2588 sum0 += dist[i];
2589 }
2590
2591 for( k = 1; k < K; k++ )
2592 {
2593 double bestSum = DBL_MAX;
2594 int bestCenter = -1;
2595
2596 for( j = 0; j < trials; j++ )
2597 {
2598 double p = (double)rng*sum0, s = 0;
2599 for( i = 0; i < N-1; i++ )
2600 if( (p -= dist[i]) <= 0 )
2601 break;
2602 int ci = i;
2603
2604 parallel_for_(Range(0, N),
2605 KMeansPPDistanceComputer(tdist2, data, dist, dims, step, step*ci));
2606 for( i = 0; i < N; i++ )
2607 {
2608 s += tdist2[i];
2609 }
2610
2611 if( s < bestSum )
2612 {
2613 bestSum = s;
2614 bestCenter = ci;
2615 std::swap(tdist, tdist2);
2616 }
2617 }
2618 centers[k] = bestCenter;
2619 sum0 = bestSum;
2620 std::swap(dist, tdist);
2621 }
2622
2623 for( k = 0; k < K; k++ )
2624 {
2625 const float* src = data + step*centers[k];
2626 float* dst = _out_centers.ptr<float>(k);
2627 for( j = 0; j < dims; j++ )
2628 dst[j] = src[j];
2629 }
2630}
2631
2632class KMeansDistanceComputer : public ParallelLoopBody
2633{
2634public:
2635 KMeansDistanceComputer( double *_distances,
2636 int *_labels,
2637 const Mat& _data,
2638 const Mat& _centers )
2639 : distances(_distances),
2640 labels(_labels),
2641 data(_data),
2642 centers(_centers)
2643 {
2644 }
2645
2646 void operator()( const Range& range ) const
2647 {
2648 const int begin = range.start;
2649 const int end = range.end;
2650 const int K = centers.rows;
2651 const int dims = centers.cols;
2652
2653 const float *sample;
2654 for( int i = begin; i<end; ++i)
2655 {
2656 sample = data.ptr<float>(i);
2657 int k_best = 0;
2658 double min_dist = DBL_MAX;
2659
2660 for( int k = 0; k < K; k++ )
2661 {
2662 const float* center = centers.ptr<float>(k);
2663 const double dist = normL2Sqr_(sample, center, dims);
2664
2665 if( min_dist > dist )
2666 {
2667 min_dist = dist;
2668 k_best = k;
2669 }
2670 }
2671
2672 distances[i] = min_dist;
2673 labels[i] = k_best;
2674 }
2675 }
2676
2677private:
2678 KMeansDistanceComputer& operator=(const KMeansDistanceComputer&); // to quiet MSVC
2679
2680 double *distances;
2681 int *labels;
2682 const Mat& data;
2683 const Mat& centers;
2684};
2685
2686}
2687
2688double cv::kmeans( InputArray _data, int K,
2689 InputOutputArray _bestLabels,
2690 TermCriteria criteria, int attempts,
2691 int flags, OutputArray _centers )
2692{
2693 const int SPP_TRIALS = 3;
2694 Mat data0 = _data.getMat();
2695 bool isrow = data0.rows == 1 && data0.channels() > 1;
2696 int N = !isrow ? data0.rows : data0.cols;
2697 int dims = (!isrow ? data0.cols : 1)*data0.channels();
2698 int type = data0.depth();
2699
2700 attempts = std::max(attempts, 1);
2701 CV_Assert( data0.dims <= 2 && type == CV_32F && K > 0 );
2702 CV_Assert( N >= K );
2703
2704 Mat data(N, dims, CV_32F, data0.data, isrow ? dims * sizeof(float) : static_cast<size_t>(data0.step));
2705
2706 _bestLabels.create(N, 1, CV_32S, -1, true);
2707
2708 Mat _labels, best_labels = _bestLabels.getMat();
2709 if( flags & CV_KMEANS_USE_INITIAL_LABELS )
2710 {
2711 CV_Assert( (best_labels.cols == 1 || best_labels.rows == 1) &&
2712 best_labels.cols*best_labels.rows == N &&
2713 best_labels.type() == CV_32S &&
2714 best_labels.isContinuous());
2715 best_labels.copyTo(_labels);
2716 }
2717 else
2718 {
2719 if( !((best_labels.cols == 1 || best_labels.rows == 1) &&
2720 best_labels.cols*best_labels.rows == N &&
2721 best_labels.type() == CV_32S &&
2722 best_labels.isContinuous()))
2723 best_labels.create(N, 1, CV_32S);
2724 _labels.create(best_labels.size(), best_labels.type());
2725 }
2726 int* labels = _labels.ptr<int>();
2727
2728 Mat centers(K, dims, type), old_centers(K, dims, type), temp(1, dims, type);
2729 vector<int> counters(K);
2730 vector<Vec2f> _box(dims);
2731 Vec2f* box = &_box[0];
2732 double best_compactness = DBL_MAX, compactness = 0;
2733 RNG& rng = theRNG();
2734 int a, iter, i, j, k;
2735
2736 if( criteria.type & TermCriteria::EPS )
2737 criteria.epsilon = std::max(criteria.epsilon, 0.);
2738 else
2739 criteria.epsilon = FLT_EPSILON;
2740 criteria.epsilon *= criteria.epsilon;
2741
2742 if( criteria.type & TermCriteria::COUNT )
2743 criteria.maxCount = std::min(std::max(criteria.maxCount, 2), 100);
2744 else
2745 criteria.maxCount = 100;
2746
2747 if( K == 1 )
2748 {
2749 attempts = 1;
2750 criteria.maxCount = 2;
2751 }
2752
2753 const float* sample = data.ptr<float>(0);
2754 for( j = 0; j < dims; j++ )
2755 box[j] = Vec2f(sample[j], sample[j]);
2756
2757 for( i = 1; i < N; i++ )
2758 {
2759 sample = data.ptr<float>(i);
2760 for( j = 0; j < dims; j++ )
2761 {
2762 float v = sample[j];
2763 box[j][0] = std::min(box[j][0], v);
2764 box[j][1] = std::max(box[j][1], v);
2765 }
2766 }
2767
2768 for( a = 0; a < attempts; a++ )
2769 {
2770 double max_center_shift = DBL_MAX;
2771 for( iter = 0;; )
2772 {
2773 swap(centers, old_centers);
2774
2775 if( iter == 0 && (a > 0 || !(flags & KMEANS_USE_INITIAL_LABELS)) )
2776 {
2777 if( flags & KMEANS_PP_CENTERS )
2778 generateCentersPP(data, centers, K, rng, SPP_TRIALS);
2779 else
2780 {
2781 for( k = 0; k < K; k++ )
2782 generateRandomCenter(_box, centers.ptr<float>(k), rng);
2783 }
2784 }
2785 else
2786 {
2787 if( iter == 0 && a == 0 && (flags & KMEANS_USE_INITIAL_LABELS) )
2788 {
2789 for( i = 0; i < N; i++ )
2790 CV_Assert( (unsigned)labels[i] < (unsigned)K );
2791 }
2792
2793 // compute centers
2794 centers = Scalar(0);
2795 for( k = 0; k < K; k++ )
2796 counters[k] = 0;
2797
2798 for( i = 0; i < N; i++ )
2799 {
2800 sample = data.ptr<float>(i);
2801 k = labels[i];
2802 float* center = centers.ptr<float>(k);
2803 j=0;
2804 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
2805 for(; j <= dims - 4; j += 4 )
2806 {
2807 float t0 = center[j] + sample[j];
2808 float t1 = center[j+1] + sample[j+1];
2809
2810 center[j] = t0;
2811 center[j+1] = t1;
2812
2813 t0 = center[j+2] + sample[j+2];
2814 t1 = center[j+3] + sample[j+3];
2815
2816 center[j+2] = t0;
2817 center[j+3] = t1;
2818 }
2819 #endif
2820 for( ; j < dims; j++ )
2821 center[j] += sample[j];
2822 counters[k]++;
2823 }
2824
2825 if( iter > 0 )
2826 max_center_shift = 0;
2827
2828 for( k = 0; k < K; k++ )
2829 {
2830 if( counters[k] != 0 )
2831 continue;
2832
2833 // if some cluster appeared to be empty then:
2834 // 1. find the biggest cluster
2835 // 2. find the farthest from the center point in the biggest cluster
2836 // 3. exclude the farthest point from the biggest cluster and form a new 1-point cluster.
2837 int max_k = 0;
2838 for( int k1 = 1; k1 < K; k1++ )
2839 {
2840 if( counters[max_k] < counters[k1] )
2841 max_k = k1;
2842 }
2843
2844 double max_dist = 0;
2845 int farthest_i = -1;
2846 float* new_center = centers.ptr<float>(k);
2847 float* old_center = centers.ptr<float>(max_k);
2848 float* _old_center = temp.ptr<float>(); // normalized
2849 float scale = 1.f/counters[max_k];
2850 for( j = 0; j < dims; j++ )
2851 _old_center[j] = old_center[j]*scale;
2852
2853 for( i = 0; i < N; i++ )
2854 {
2855 if( labels[i] != max_k )
2856 continue;
2857 sample = data.ptr<float>(i);
2858 double dist = normL2Sqr_(sample, _old_center, dims);
2859
2860 if( max_dist <= dist )
2861 {
2862 max_dist = dist;
2863 farthest_i = i;
2864 }
2865 }
2866
2867 counters[max_k]--;
2868 counters[k]++;
2869 labels[farthest_i] = k;
2870 sample = data.ptr<float>(farthest_i);
2871
2872 for( j = 0; j < dims; j++ )
2873 {
2874 old_center[j] -= sample[j];
2875 new_center[j] += sample[j];
2876 }
2877 }
2878
2879 for( k = 0; k < K; k++ )
2880 {
2881 float* center = centers.ptr<float>(k);
2882 CV_Assert( counters[k] != 0 );
2883
2884 float scale = 1.f/counters[k];
2885 for( j = 0; j < dims; j++ )
2886 center[j] *= scale;
2887
2888 if( iter > 0 )
2889 {
2890 double dist = 0;
2891 const float* old_center = old_centers.ptr<float>(k);
2892 for( j = 0; j < dims; j++ )
2893 {
2894 double t = center[j] - old_center[j];
2895 dist += t*t;
2896 }
2897 max_center_shift = std::max(max_center_shift, dist);
2898 }
2899 }
2900 }
2901
2902 if( ++iter == MAX(criteria.maxCount, 2) || max_center_shift <= criteria.epsilon )
2903 break;
2904
2905 // assign labels
2906 Mat dists(1, N, CV_64F);
2907 double* dist = dists.ptr<double>(0);
2908 parallel_for_(Range(0, N),
2909 KMeansDistanceComputer(dist, labels, data, centers));
2910 compactness = 0;
2911 for( i = 0; i < N; i++ )
2912 {
2913 compactness += dist[i];
2914 }
2915 }
2916
2917 if( compactness < best_compactness )
2918 {
2919 best_compactness = compactness;
2920 if( _centers.needed() )
2921 centers.copyTo(_centers);
2922 _labels.copyTo(best_labels);
2923 }
2924 }
2925
2926 return best_compactness;
2927}

2990CV_IMPL CvArr*
2991cvRange( CvArr* arr, double start, double end )
2992{
2993 int ok = 0;
2994
2995 CvMat stub, *mat = (CvMat*)arr;
2996 double delta;
2997 int type, step;
2998 double val = start;
2999 int i, j;
3000 int rows, cols;
3001
3002 if( !CV_IS_MAT(mat) )
3003 mat = cvGetMat( mat, &stub);
3004
3005 rows = mat->rows;
3006 cols = mat->cols;
3007 type = CV_MAT_TYPE(mat->type);
3008 delta = (end-start)/(rows*cols);
3009
3010 if( CV_IS_MAT_CONT(mat->type) )
3011 {
3012 cols *= rows;
3013 rows = 1;
3014 step = 1;
3015 }
3016 else
3017 step = mat->step / CV_ELEM_SIZE(type);
3018
3019 if( type == CV_32SC1 )
3020 {
3021 int* idata = mat->data.i;
3022 int ival = cvRound(val), idelta = cvRound(delta);
3023
3024 if( fabs(val - ival) < DBL_EPSILON &&
3025 fabs(delta - idelta) < DBL_EPSILON )
3026 {
3027 for( i = 0; i < rows; i++, idata += step )
3028 for( j = 0; j < cols; j++, ival += idelta )
3029 idata[j] = ival;
3030 }
3031 else
3032 {
3033 for( i = 0; i < rows; i++, idata += step )
3034 for( j = 0; j < cols; j++, val += delta )
3035 idata[j] = cvRound(val);
3036 }
3037 }
3038 else if( type == CV_32FC1 )
3039 {
3040 float* fdata = mat->data.fl;
3041 for( i = 0; i < rows; i++, fdata += step )
3042 for( j = 0; j < cols; j++, val += delta )
3043 fdata[j] = (float)val;
3044 }
3045 else
3046 CV_Error( CV_StsUnsupportedFormat, "The function only supports 32sC1 and 32fC1 datatypes" );
3047
3048 ok = 1;
3049 return ok ? arr : 0;
3050}

3152
3153void NAryMatIterator::init(const Mat** _arrays, Mat* _planes, uchar** _ptrs, int _narrays)
3154{
3155 CV_Assert( _arrays && (_ptrs || _planes) );
3156 int i, j, d1=0, i0 = -1, d = -1;
3157
3158 arrays = _arrays;
3159 ptrs = _ptrs;
3160 planes = _planes;
3161 narrays = _narrays;
3162 nplanes = 0;
3163 size = 0;
3164
3165 if( narrays < 0 )
3166 {
3167 for( i = 0; _arrays[i] != 0; i++ )
3168 ;
3169 narrays = i;
3170 CV_Assert(narrays <= 1000);
3171 }
3172
3173 iterdepth = 0;
3174
3175 for( i = 0; i < narrays; i++ )
3176 {
3177 CV_Assert(arrays[i] != 0);
3178 const Mat& A = *arrays[i];
3179 if( ptrs )
3180 ptrs[i] = A.data;
3181
3182 if( !A.data )
3183 continue;
3184
3185 if( i0 < 0 )
3186 {
3187 i0 = i;
3188 d = A.dims;
3189
3190 // find the first dimensionality which is different from 1;
3191 // in any of the arrays the first "d1" step do not affect the continuity
3192 for( d1 = 0; d1 < d; d1++ )
3193 if( A.size[d1] > 1 )
3194 break;
3195 }
3196 else
3197 CV_Assert( A.size == arrays[i0]->size );
3198
3199 if( !A.isContinuous() )
3200 {
3201 CV_Assert( A.step[d-1] == A.elemSize() );
3202 for( j = d-1; j > d1; j-- )
3203 if( A.step[j]*A.size[j] < A.step[j-1] )
3204 break;
3205 iterdepth = std::max(iterdepth, j);
3206 }
3207 }
3208
3209 if( i0 >= 0 )
3210 {
3211 size = arrays[i0]->size[d-1];
3212 for( j = d-1; j > iterdepth; j-- )
3213 {
3214 int64 total1 = (int64)size*arrays[i0]->size[j-1];
3215 if( total1 != (int)total1 )
3216 break;
3217 size = (int)total1;
3218 }
3219
3220 iterdepth = j;
3221 if( iterdepth == d1 )
3222 iterdepth = 0;
3223
3224 nplanes = 1;
3225 for( j = iterdepth-1; j >= 0; j-- )
3226 nplanes *= arrays[i0]->size[j];
3227 }
3228 else
3229 iterdepth = 0;
3230
3231 idx = 0;
3232
3233 if( !planes )
3234 return;
3235
3236 for( i = 0; i < narrays; i++ )
3237 {
3238 CV_Assert(arrays[i] != 0);
3239 const Mat& A = *arrays[i];
3240
3241 if( !A.data )
3242 {
3243 planes[i] = Mat();
3244 continue;
3245 }
3246
3247 planes[i] = Mat(1, (int)size, A.type(), A.data);
3248 }
3249}
3250
3251
3252NAryMatIterator& NAryMatIterator::operator ++()
3253{
3254 if( idx >= nplanes-1 )
3255 return *this;
3256 ++idx;
3257
3258 if( iterdepth == 1 )
3259 {
3260 if( ptrs )
3261 {
3262 for( int i = 0; i < narrays; i++ )
3263 {
3264 if( !ptrs[i] )
3265 continue;
3266 ptrs[i] = arrays[i]->data + arrays[i]->step[0]*idx;
3267 }
3268 }
3269 if( planes )
3270 {
3271 for( int i = 0; i < narrays; i++ )
3272 {
3273 if( !planes[i].data )
3274 continue;
3275 planes[i].data = arrays[i]->data + arrays[i]->step[0]*idx;
3276 }
3277 }
3278 }
3279 else
3280 {
3281 for( int i = 0; i < narrays; i++ )
3282 {
3283 const Mat& A = *arrays[i];
3284 if( !A.data )
3285 continue;
3286 int _idx = (int)idx;
3287 uchar* data = A.data;
3288 for( int j = iterdepth-1; j >= 0 && _idx > 0; j-- )
3289 {
3290 int szi = A.size[j], t = _idx/szi;
3291 data += (_idx - t * szi)*A.step[j];
3292 _idx = t;
3293 }
3294 if( ptrs )
3295 ptrs[i] = data;
3296 if( planes )
3297 planes[i].data = data;
3298 }
3299 }
3300
3301 return *this;
3302}

3325
3326void MatConstIterator::pos(int* _idx) const
3327{
3328 CV_Assert(m != 0 && _idx);
3329 ptrdiff_t ofs = ptr - m->data;
3330 for( int i = 0; i < m->dims; i++ )
3331 {
3332 size_t s = m->step[i], v = ofs/s;
3333 ofs -= v*s;
3334 _idx[i] = (int)v;
3335 }
3336}
3337
3338ptrdiff_t MatConstIterator::lpos() const
3339{
3340 if(!m)
3341 return 0;
3342 if( m->isContinuous() )
3343 return (ptr - sliceStart)/elemSize;
3344 ptrdiff_t ofs = ptr - m->data;
3345 int i, d = m->dims;
3346 if( d == 2 )
3347 {
3348 ptrdiff_t y = ofs/m->step[0];
3349 return y*m->cols + (ofs - y*m->step[0])/elemSize;
3350 }
3351 ptrdiff_t result = 0;
3352 for( i = 0; i < d; i++ )
3353 {
3354 size_t s = m->step[i], v = ofs/s;
3355 ofs -= v*s;
3356 result = result*m->size[i] + v;
3357 }
3358 return result;
3359}
3360
3361void MatConstIterator::seek(ptrdiff_t ofs, bool relative)
3362{
3363 if( m->isContinuous() )
3364 {
3365 ptr = (relative ? ptr : sliceStart) + ofs*elemSize;
3366 if( ptr < sliceStart )
3367 ptr = sliceStart;
3368 else if( ptr > sliceEnd )
3369 ptr = sliceEnd;
3370 return;
3371 }
3372
3373 int d = m->dims;
3374 if( d == 2 )
3375 {
3376 ptrdiff_t ofs0, y;
3377 if( relative )
3378 {
3379 ofs0 = ptr - m->data;
3380 y = ofs0/m->step[0];
3381 ofs += y*m->cols + (ofs0 - y*m->step[0])/elemSize;
3382 }
3383 y = ofs/m->cols;
3384 int y1 = std::min(std::max((int)y, 0), m->rows-1);
3385 sliceStart = m->data + y1*m->step[0];
3386 sliceEnd = sliceStart + m->cols*elemSize;
3387 ptr = y < 0 ? sliceStart : y >= m->rows ? sliceEnd :
3388 sliceStart + (ofs - y*m->cols)*elemSize;
3389 return;
3390 }
3391
3392 if( relative )
3393 ofs += lpos();
3394
3395 if( ofs < 0 )
3396 ofs = 0;
3397
3398 int szi = m->size[d-1];
3399 ptrdiff_t t = ofs/szi;
3400 int v = (int)(ofs - t*szi);
3401 ofs = t;
3402 ptr = m->data + v*elemSize;
3403 sliceStart = m->data;
3404
3405 for( int i = d-2; i >= 0; i-- )
3406 {
3407 szi = m->size[i];
3408 t = ofs/szi;
3409 v = (int)(ofs - t*szi);
3410 ofs = t;
3411 sliceStart += v*m->step[i];
3412 }
3413
3414 sliceEnd = sliceStart + m->size[d-1]*elemSize;
3415 if( ofs > 0 )
3416 ptr = sliceEnd;
3417 else
3418 ptr = sliceStart + (ptr - m->data);
3419}
3420
3421void MatConstIterator::seek(const int* _idx, bool relative)
3422{
3423 int i, d = m->dims;
3424 ptrdiff_t ofs = 0;
3425 if( !_idx )
3426 ;
3427 else if( d == 2 )
3428 ofs = _idx[0]*m->size[1] + _idx[1];
3429 else
3430 {
3431 for( i = 0; i < d; i++ )
3432 ofs = ofs*m->size[i] + _idx[i];
3433 }
3434 seek(ofs, relative);
3435}
3436
3437ptrdiff_t operator - (const MatConstIterator& b, const MatConstIterator& a)
3438{
3439 if( a.m != b.m )
3440 return INT_MAX;
3441 if( a.sliceEnd == b.sliceEnd )
3442 return (b.ptr - a.ptr)/static_cast<ptrdiff_t>(b.elemSize);
3443
3444 return b.lpos() - a.lpos();
3445}

3449template<typename T1, typename T2> void
3450convertData_(const void* _from, void* _to, int cn)
3451{
3452 const T1* from = (const T1*)_from;
3453 T2* to = (T2*)_to;
3454 if( cn == 1 )
3455 *to = saturate_cast<T2>(*from);
3456 else
3457 for( int i = 0; i < cn; i++ )
3458 to[i] = saturate_cast<T2>(from[i]);
3459}
3460
3461template<typename T1, typename T2> void
3462convertScaleData_(const void* _from, void* _to, int cn, double alpha, double beta)
3463{
3464 const T1* from = (const T1*)_from;
3465 T2* to = (T2*)_to;
3466 if( cn == 1 )
3467 *to = saturate_cast<T2>(*from*alpha + beta);
3468 else
3469 for( int i = 0; i < cn; i++ )
3470 to[i] = saturate_cast<T2>(from[i]*alpha + beta);
3471}

3565static inline void copyElem(const uchar* from, uchar* to, size_t elemSize)
3566{
3567 size_t i;
3568 for( i = 0; i + sizeof(int) <= elemSize; i += sizeof(int) )
3569 *(int*)(to + i) = *(const int*)(from + i);
3570 for( ; i < elemSize; i++ )
3571 to[i] = from[i];
3572}

3574static inline bool isZeroElem(const uchar* data, size_t elemSize)
3575{
3576 size_t i;
3577 for( i = 0; i + sizeof(int) <= elemSize; i += sizeof(int) )
3578 if( *(int*)(data + i) != 0 )
3579 return false;
3580 for( ; i < elemSize; i++ )
3581 if( data[i] != 0 )
3582 return false;
3583 return true;
3584}

3614SparseMat::SparseMat(const Mat& m)
3615: flags(MAGIC_VAL), hdr(0)
3616{
3617 create( m.dims, m.size, m.type() );
3618
3619 int i, idx[CV_MAX_DIM] = {0}, d = m.dims, lastSize = m.size[d - 1];
3620 size_t esz = m.elemSize();
3621 uchar* dptr = m.data;
3622
3623 for(;;)
3624 {
3625 for( i = 0; i < lastSize; i++, dptr += esz )
3626 {
3627 if( isZeroElem(dptr, esz) )
3628 continue;
3629 idx[d-1] = i;
3630 uchar* to = newNode(idx, hash(idx));
3631 copyElem( dptr, to, esz );
3632 }
3633
3634 for( i = d - 2; i >= 0; i-- )
3635 {
3636 dptr += m.step[i] - m.size[i+1]*m.step[i+1];
3637 if( ++idx[i] < m.size[i] )
3638 break;
3639 idx[i] = 0;
3640 }
3641 if( i < 0 )
3642 break;
3643 }

3981 if( nidx )
3982 removeNode(hidx, nidx, previdx);
3983}

3985void SparseMat::resizeHashTab(size_t newsize)
3986{
3987 newsize = std::max(newsize, (size_t)8);
3988 if((newsize & (newsize-1)) != 0)
3989 newsize = (size_t)1 << cvCeil(std::log((double)newsize)/CV_LOG2);
3990
3991 size_t i, hsize = hdr->hashtab.size();
3992 vector<size_t> _newh(newsize);
3993 size_t* newh = &_newh[0];
3994 for( i = 0; i < newsize; i++ )
3995 newh[i] = 0;
3996 uchar* pool = &hdr->pool[0];
3997 for( i = 0; i < hsize; i++ )
3998 {
3999 size_t nidx = hdr->hashtab[i];
4000 while( nidx )
4001 {
4002 Node* elem = (Node*)(pool + nidx);
4003 size_t next = elem->next;
4004 size_t newhidx = elem->hashval & (newsize - 1);
4005 elem->next = newh[newhidx];
4006 newh[newhidx] = nidx;
4007 nidx = next;
4008 }
4009 }
4010 hdr->hashtab = _newh;
4011}

4013uchar* SparseMat::newNode(const int* idx, size_t hashval)
4014{
4015 const int HASH_MAX_FILL_FACTOR=3;
4016 assert(hdr);
4017 size_t hsize = hdr->hashtab.size();
4018 if( ++hdr->nodeCount > hsize*HASH_MAX_FILL_FACTOR )
4019 {
4020 resizeHashTab(std::max(hsize*2, (size_t)8));
4021 hsize = hdr->hashtab.size();
4022 }
4023
4024 if( !hdr->freeList )
4025 {
4026 size_t i, nsz = hdr->nodeSize, psize = hdr->pool.size(),
4027 newpsize = std::max(psize*2, 8*nsz);
4028 hdr->pool.resize(newpsize);
4029 uchar* pool = &hdr->pool[0];
4030 hdr->freeList = std::max(psize, nsz);
4031 for( i = hdr->freeList; i < newpsize - nsz; i += nsz )
4032 ((Node*)(pool + i))->next = i + nsz;
4033 ((Node*)(pool + i))->next = 0;
4034 }
4035 size_t nidx = hdr->freeList;
4036 Node* elem = (Node*)&hdr->pool[nidx];
4037 hdr->freeList = elem->next;
4038 elem->hashval = hashval;
4039 size_t hidx = hashval & (hsize - 1);
4040 elem->next = hdr->hashtab[hidx];
4041 hdr->hashtab[hidx] = nidx;
4042
4043 int i, d = hdr->dims;
4044 for( i = 0; i < d; i++ )
4045 elem->idx[i] = idx[i];
4046 size_t esz = elemSize();
4047 uchar* p = &value<uchar>(elem);
4048 if( esz == sizeof(float) )
4049 *((float*)p) = 0.f;
4050 else if( esz == sizeof(double) )
4051 *((double*)p) = 0.;
4052 else
4053 memset(p, 0, esz);
4054
4055 return p;
4056}

4059void SparseMat::removeNode(size_t hidx, size_t nidx, size_t previdx)
4060{
4061 Node* n = node(nidx);
4062 if( previdx )
4063 {
4064 Node* prev = node(previdx);
4065 prev->next = n->next;
4066 }
4067 else
4068 hdr->hashtab[hidx] = n->next;
4069 n->next = hdr->freeList;
4070 hdr->freeList = nidx;
4071 --hdr->nodeCount;
4072}

4075SparseMatConstIterator::SparseMatConstIterator(const SparseMat* _m)
4076: m((SparseMat*)_m), hashidx(0), ptr(0)
4077{
4078 if(!_m || !_m->hdr)
4079 return;
4080 SparseMat::Hdr& hdr = *m->hdr;
4081 const vector<size_t>& htab = hdr.hashtab;
4082 size_t i, hsize = htab.size();
4083 for( i = 0; i < hsize; i++ )
4084 {
4085 size_t nidx = htab[i];
4086 if( nidx )
4087 {
4088 hashidx = i;
4089 ptr = &hdr.pool[nidx] + hdr.valueOffset;
4090 return;
4091 }
4092 }
4093}
4094
4095SparseMatConstIterator& SparseMatConstIterator::operator ++()
4096{
4097 if( !ptr || !m || !m->hdr )
4098 return *this;
4099 SparseMat::Hdr& hdr = *m->hdr;
4100 size_t next = ((const SparseMat::Node*)(ptr - hdr.valueOffset))->next;
4101 if( next )
4102 {
4103 ptr = &hdr.pool[next] + hdr.valueOffset;
4104 return *this;
4105 }
4106 size_t i = hashidx + 1, sz = hdr.hashtab.size();
4107 for( ; i < sz; i++ )
4108 {
4109 size_t nidx = hdr.hashtab[i];
4110 if( nidx )
4111 {
4112 hashidx = i;
4113 ptr = &hdr.pool[nidx] + hdr.valueOffset;
4114 return *this;
4115 }
4116 }
4117 hashidx = sz;
4118 ptr = 0;
4119 return *this;
4120}

4123double norm( const SparseMat& src, int normType )
4124{
4125 SparseMatConstIterator it = src.begin();
4126
4127 size_t i, N = src.nzcount();
4128 normType &= NORM_TYPE_MASK;
4129 int type = src.type();
4130 double result = 0;
4131
4132 CV_Assert( normType == NORM_INF || normType == NORM_L1 || normType == NORM_L2 );
4133
4134 if( type == CV_32F )
4135 {
4136 if( normType == NORM_INF )
4137 for( i = 0; i < N; i++, ++it )
4138 result = std::max(result, std::abs((double)*(const float*)it.ptr));
4139 else if( normType == NORM_L1 )
4140 for( i = 0; i < N; i++, ++it )
4141 result += std::abs(*(const float*)it.ptr);
4142 else
4143 for( i = 0; i < N; i++, ++it )
4144 {
4145 double v = *(const float*)it.ptr;
4146 result += v*v;
4147 }
4148 }
4149 else if( type == CV_64F )
4150 {
4151 if( normType == NORM_INF )
4152 for( i = 0; i < N; i++, ++it )
4153 result = std::max(result, std::abs(*(const double*)it.ptr));
4154 else if( normType == NORM_L1 )
4155 for( i = 0; i < N; i++, ++it )
4156 result += std::abs(*(const double*)it.ptr);
4157 else
4158 for( i = 0; i < N; i++, ++it )
4159 {
4160 double v = *(const double*)it.ptr;
4161 result += v*v;
4162 }
4163 }
4164 else
4165 CV_Error( CV_StsUnsupportedFormat, "Only 32f and 64f are supported" );
4166
4167 if( normType == NORM_L2 )
4168 result = std::sqrt(result);
4169 return result;
4170}

4172void minMaxLoc( const SparseMat& src, double* _minval, double* _maxval, int* _minidx, int* _maxidx )
4173{
4174 SparseMatConstIterator it = src.begin();
4175 size_t i, N = src.nzcount(), d = src.hdr ? src.hdr->dims : 0;
4176 int type = src.type();
4177 const int *minidx = 0, *maxidx = 0;
4178
4179 if( type == CV_32F )
4180 {
4181 float minval = FLT_MAX, maxval = -FLT_MAX;
4182 for( i = 0; i < N; i++, ++it )
4183 {
4184 float v = *(const float*)it.ptr;
4185 if( v < minval )
4186 {
4187 minval = v;
4188 minidx = it.node()->idx;
4189 }
4190 if( v > maxval )
4191 {
4192 maxval = v;
4193 maxidx = it.node()->idx;
4194 }
4195 }
4196 if( _minval )
4197 *_minval = minval;
4198 if( _maxval )
4199 *_maxval = maxval;
4200 }
4201 else if( type == CV_64F )
4202 {
4203 double minval = DBL_MAX, maxval = -DBL_MAX;
4204 for( i = 0; i < N; i++, ++it )
4205 {
4206 double v = *(const double*)it.ptr;
4207 if( v < minval )
4208 {
4209 minval = v;
4210 minidx = it.node()->idx;
4211 }
4212 if( v > maxval )
4213 {
4214 maxval = v;
4215 maxidx = it.node()->idx;
4216 }
4217 }
4218 if( _minval )
4219 *_minval = minval;
4220 if( _maxval )
4221 *_maxval = maxval;
4222 }
4223 else
4224 CV_Error( CV_StsUnsupportedFormat, "Only 32f and 64f are supported" );
4225
4226 if( _minidx )
4227 for( i = 0; i < d; i++ )
4228 _minidx[i] = minidx[i];
4229 if( _maxidx )
4230 for( i = 0; i < d; i++ )
4231 _maxidx[i] = maxidx[i];
4232}

4235void normalize( const SparseMat& src, SparseMat& dst, double a, int norm_type )
4236{
4237 double scale = 1;
4238 if( norm_type == CV_L2 || norm_type == CV_L1 || norm_type == CV_C )
4239 {
4240 scale = norm( src, norm_type );
4241 scale = scale > DBL_EPSILON ? a/scale : 0.;
4242 }
4243 else
4244 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "Unknown/unsupported norm type" );
4245
4246 src.convertTo( dst, -1, scale );
4247}

4251void RotatedRect::points(Point2f pt[]) const
4252{
4253 double _angle = angle*CV_PI/180.;
4254 float b = (float)cos(_angle)*0.5f;
4255 float a = (float)sin(_angle)*0.5f;
4256
4257 pt[0].x = center.x - a*size.height - b*size.width;
4258 pt[0].y = center.y + b*size.height - a*size.width;
4259 pt[1].x = center.x + a*size.height - b*size.width;
4260 pt[1].y = center.y - b*size.height - a*size.width;
4261 pt[2].x = 2*center.x - pt[0].x;
4262 pt[2].y = 2*center.y - pt[0].y;
4263 pt[3].x = 2*center.x - pt[1].x;
4264 pt[3].y = 2*center.y - pt[1].y;
4265}
4266
4267Rect RotatedRect::boundingRect() const
4268{
4269 Point2f pt[4];
4270 points(pt);
4271 Rect r(cvFloor(min(min(min(pt[0].x, pt[1].x), pt[2].x), pt[3].x)),
4272 cvFloor(min(min(min(pt[0].y, pt[1].y), pt[2].y), pt[3].y)),
4273 cvCeil(max(max(max(pt[0].x, pt[1].x), pt[2].x), pt[3].x)),
4274 cvCeil(max(max(max(pt[0].y, pt[1].y), pt[2].y), pt[3].y)));
4275 r.width -= r.x - 1;
4276 r.height -= r.y - 1;
4277 return r;
4278}
